INSERT INTO `ksshelp` VALUES (1,33,'d','en_us','07.02.01','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/01-General/GeneralHome.html','Suppliers.General Information','Suppliers - General Information','Suppliers - General Information\r \r \r \r \r Suppliers - General Information\r This section covers the activites realted to your suppliers.\r Accounts - \r Purchase Orders - \r Quotes - \r Purchases - \r Payments - \r POP - \r Credit Memos - \r Supplier Status -'),(2,6,'d','en_us','07.02.02.01','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/02-Accounts/01-NewAccount.html','Supplier Account.Entering','Entering a Supplier Account','Entering a Supplier Account\r \r \r \r \r  Entering a Supplier Account \r Supplier accounts include any outside organization that you acquire goods or services from. Generally, they are organizations that you make payments to. \r NOTE: Supplier accounts may be created at time of purchase by entering the required information and checking the Add/Update button in the Purchase/Receive, Payment or Purchase Order form. In this case, an unique account ID must be entered and the account will be created using the standard terms, default Purchase GL account, no User ID, Account Number, Federal ID number, or additional shipping or billing addresses. \r To create a new account:\r \r   Select Suppliers-&gt;New Supplier or Select the New icon form the Suppliers-&gt;Maintain Suppliers page.\r    Enter an unique Supplier ID. The Supplier ID (or short name) is an unique field to identify this supplier form all other suppliers. Maximum length is 20 characters.\r   Enter remaining Primary Contact  and Main Mailing (billing) Address information. Required fields are identified by a (*).\r   Enter the default purchase account. This is typically an accounts payable general ledger account type.\r   Enter an user id assigned to this supplier. \r   Enter your account number with this supplier. This number can be used for purchase orders, checks to reference your account to the supplier.\r    Enter the Tax or Federal ID number. generally used for tax purposes.\r    If the supplier can ship from multiple locations, additional ship from addresses can be added in the Shipping Addresses form area. Unlimited shipping addresses may be assigned to a supplier but only one may be added at a time.\r   Enter the payment terms you have with the supplier. The defaults are preloaded but may be over-ridden on a supplier by supplier basis. \r   If the supplier has additional remit to (billing) addresses, they may be added in the Billing Addresses form area. Unlimited billing addresses may be assigned to a supplier but only one may be added at a time. \r   Press the Save icon and the record will be saved and you will be returned to the Maintain Suppliers page. \r \r Related Topics\r Suppliers\r   Updating a supplier account\r   Deleting a supplier account\r Setting up a supplier credit limit\r Purchase Orders\r Deleting a purchase order\r   Closing a purchase order\r Purchase/Receive Inventory \r Receiving items from a purchase order\r Reports and Forms \r   Checking supplier balances'),(3,6,'d','en_us','07.02.02.02','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/02-Accounts/02-EditAccount.html','Supplier Account.Editing','Editing a Supplier Account','Editing a Supplier Account\r \r \r \r \r Editing a Supplier Account\r To edit a supplier record:\r \r   Select Suppliers-&gt;Maintain Suppliers page.\r   Select the Edit icon next to the supplier to edit. A search box has been provided to quickly locate the supplier.\r   Edit/update/change any fields for the supplier.\r   Add/Delete any additional shipping or billing addresses.\r   Press the Save button to save the changes. You will be returned to the Maintain Suppliers page. \r \r Related Topics\r Suppliers\r  Adding a new supplier account \r   Deleting a supplier account \r Setting up a supplier credit limit\r Purchase Orders\r Entering  a purchase order\r   Deleting a purchase order\r   Closing a purchase order\r Reports and Forms \r Checking supplier balances\r \r &nbsp;'),(4,6,'d','en_us','07.02.02.03','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/02-Accounts/03-DeleteAccount.html','Supplier Account.Deleting','Deleting a Supplier Account','Deleting a Supplier Account\r \r \r \r \r  Deleting a Supplier Account \r NOTE: Suppliers cannot be deleted if they have a journal entry associated with them. \r To delete a supplier record:\r \r   Select Suppliers-&gt;Maintain Suppliers page.\r   Select the Delete icon next to the supplier to delete. A search box has been provided to quickly locate the supplier.\r   Confirm the deletion and you will be returned to the Maintain Suppliers page. \r \r Related Topics\r Suppliers\r  Adding a new supplier account \r Editing a supplier account \r Purchase Orders\r   Deleting a purchase order\r   Closing a purchase order\r Reports and Forms \r Checking supplier balances\r \r &nbsp;'),(5,6,'d','en_us','07.02.02.04','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/02-Accounts/04-PaymentTerms.html','Supplier Accounts.Payment Terms','Supplier Payment Terms','Supplier Payment Terms\r \r \r \r \r Supplier Payment Terms\r Supplier payment terms may be set up through the configuration screen. The terms set up will be applied as the default terms for all new supplier accounts. Additionally, existing accounts with out terms defined (or \'Use Standard Terms\') will track the terms defined in the configuration setup definitions. Individual supplier terms may also be set up for suppliers whose terms are different from the standard terms. Terms may also be set up for specific purchases through the Purchase Order/Purchase procedure. \r Setting up Default Terms \r \r   Select Company-&gt;Supplier Defaults.\r   Edit the fields as necessary. The terms type defaults to the standard X% discount in Y days, Net Z days.\r   Set the default supplier credit limit to use. \r \r Setting up Supplier Specific Payment Terms\r \r    Select  Suppliers-&gt;Maintain Suppliers. \r   Search for the supplier whose terms you want to change and press the edit icon to reach the detailed page.\r    Under the section titled Payment Terms, check the radio button for the terms type to apply to this supplier.\r   Depending on the terms type selected, the Discount, Due In, Net and date fields will be active. Fill in the fields for the terms type selected.\r   Enter the credit limit for the current supplier.\r   Press the Save icon to save the changes.\r \r Setting Payment Terms for a Single Purchase\r \r   Select Suppliers-&gt;Purchase/Receive (or Purchase Order, Supplier Quote).\r   On the form select the Open icon next to the terms field. A popup window will open with the current terms selected.\r   Change the terms as necessary and press Save to enter the new terms into the form.\r \r Related Topics\r Suppliers\r  Adding a new supplier account\r Editing a supplier account\r Purchase Orders\r   Deleting a purchase order\r   Closing a purchase order\r Reports and Forms \r Checking supplier balance\r &nbsp;'),(6,33,'0','en_us','07.02.02','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/02-Accounts/AccountsHome.html','Suppliers.Accounts','Suppliers - Accounts','Suppliers - Accounts\r \r \r \r \r Suppliers - Accounts \r Supplier accounts contain information about your suppliers of inventory, services and other purchases required for your business. The procedures to setup, edit and delete supplier accounts is similar to that for customers within KSSBooks. \r Supplier Account features:\r \r   Default global settings for purchase account and terms; customizable for each individual supplier\r   Unlimited billing addresses\r   Unlimited shipping addresses\r    Individual purchase rep default assignment \r   Free-form notes field \r \r Related Topics\r Suppliers\r Entering a new supplier \r Updating supplier information\r Deleting a supplier \r Setting supplier payment terms and credit limits \r Purchase  Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r   Deleting a purchase order\r   Closing a purchase order\r Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r   Receiving inventory directly from a supplier\r Other Supplier Actions \r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r   Writing a check to a supplier\r   Issuing a supplier credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking supplier balance\r &nbsp;'),(7,6,'d','en_us','07.02.02.01','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/02-Contacts/01-NewContact.html','Supplier Contacts.Entering','Entering a Supplier Contact','Entering a Supplier Contact\r \r \r \r \r  Entering a Supplier Contact \r Supplier contacts include any outside organization that you acquire goods or services from. Generally, they are organizations that you make payments to. \r NOTE: Supplier contacts may be created at time of purchase by entering the required information and checking the Add/Update button in the Purchase/Receive, Payment or Purchase Order form. In this case, an unique contact ID must be entered and the contact will be created using the standard terms, default Purchase GL account, no User ID, Account Number, Federal ID number, or additional shipping or billing addresses. \r To create a new contact:\r \r   Select Suppliers-&gt;New Supplier or Select the New icon form the Suppliers-&gt;Maintain Suppliers page.\r    Enter an unique Supplier ID. The Supplier ID (or short name) is an unique field to identify this supplier form all other suppliers. Maximum length is 20 characters.\r   Enter remaining Primary Contact  and Main Mailing (billing) Address information. Required fields are identified by a (*).\r   Enter the default purchase account. This is typically an accounts payable general ledger account type.\r   Enter an user id assigned to this supplier. \r   Enter your account number with this supplier. This number can be used for purchase orders, checks to reference your account to the supplier.\r    Enter the Tax or Federal ID number. generally used for tax purposes.\r    If the supplier can ship from multiple locations, additional ship from addresses can be added in the Shipping Addresses form area. Unlimited shipping addresses may be assigned to a supplier but only one may be added at a time.\r   Enter the payment terms you have with the supplier. The defaults are preloaded but may be over-ridden on a supplier by supplier basis. \r   If the supplier has additional remit to (billing) addresses, they may be added in the Billing Addresses form area. Unlimited billing addresses may be assigned to a supplier but only one may be added at a time. \r   Press the Save icon and the record will be saved and you will be returned to the Maintain Suppliers page. \r \r Related Topics\r Suppliers\r   Updating a supplier contact\r   Deleting a supplier contact\r Setting up a supplier credit limit\r Purchase Orders\r Deleting a purchase order\r   Closing a purchase order\r Purchase/Receive Inventory \r Receiving items from a purchase order\r Reports and Forms \r   Checking supplier balances'),(8,6,'d','en_us','07.02.02.02','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/02-Contacts/02-EditContact.html','Supplier Contacts.Editing','Editing a Supplier Contact','Editing a Supplier Contact\r \r \r \r \r Editing a Supplier Contact\r To edit a supplier record:\r \r   Select Suppliers-&gt;Maintain Suppliers page.\r   Select the Edit icon next to the supplier to edit. A search box has been provided to quickly locate the supplier.\r   Edit/update/change any fields for the supplier.\r   Add/Delete any additional shipping or billing addresses.\r   Press the Save button to save the changes. You will be returned to the Maintain Suppliers page. \r \r Related Topics\r Suppliers\r  Adding a new supplier contact \r   Deleting a supplier contact \r Setting up a supplier credit limit\r Purchase Orders\r Entering  a purchase order\r   Deleting a purchase order\r   Closing a purchase order\r Reports and Forms \r Checking supplier balances\r \r &nbsp;'),(9,6,'d','en_us','07.02.02.03','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/02-Contacts/03-DeleteContact.html','Supplier Contacts.Deleting','Deleting a Supplier Contact','Deleting a Supplier Contact\r \r \r \r \r  Deleting a Supplier Contact \r NOTE: Suppliers cannot be deleted if they have a journal entry associated with them. \r To delete a supplier record:\r \r   Select Suppliers-&gt;Maintain Suppliers page.\r   Select the Delete icon next to the supplier to delete. A search box has been provided to quickly locate the supplier.\r   Confirm the deletion and you will be returned to the Maintain Suppliers page. \r \r Related Topics\r Suppliers\r  Adding a new supplier contact \r Editing a supplier contact \r Purchase Orders\r   Deleting a purchase order\r   Closing a purchase order\r Reports and Forms \r Checking supplier balances\r \r &nbsp;'),(10,6,'d','en_us','07.02.02.04','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/02-Contacts/04-PaymentTerms.html','Supplier Accounts.Payment Terms','Supplier Payment Terms','Supplier Payment Terms\r \r \r \r \r Supplier Payment Terms\r Supplier payment terms may be set up through the configuration screen. The terms set up will be applied as the default terms for all new supplier contacts. Additionally, existing contacts with out terms defined (or \'Use Standard Terms\') will track the terms defined in the configuration setup definitions. Individual supplier terms may also be set up for suppliers whose terms are different from the standard terms. Terms may also be set up for specific purchases through the Purchase Order/Purchase procedure. \r Setting up Default Terms \r \r   Select Company-&gt;Supplier Defaults.\r   Edit the fields as necessary. The terms type defaults to the standard X% discount in Y days, Net Z days.\r   Set the default supplier credit limit to use. \r \r Setting up Supplier Specific Payment Terms\r \r    Select  Suppliers-&gt;Maintain Suppliers. \r   Search for the supplier whose terms you want to change and press the edit icon to reach the detailed page.\r    Under the section titled Payment Terms, check the radio button for the terms type to apply to this supplier.\r   Depending on the terms type selected, the Discount, Due In, Net and date fields will be active. Fill in the fields for the terms type selected.\r   Enter the credit limit for the current supplier.\r   Press the Save icon to save the changes.\r \r Setting Payment Terms for a Single Purchase\r \r   Select Suppliers-&gt;Purchase/Receive (or Purchase Order, Supplier Quote).\r   On the form select the Open icon next to the terms field. A popup window will open with the current terms selected.\r   Change the terms as necessary and press Save to enter the new terms into the form.\r \r Related Topics\r Suppliers\r  Adding a new supplier contact\r Editing a supplier contact\r Purchase Orders\r   Deleting a purchase order\r   Closing a purchase order\r Reports and Forms \r Checking supplier balance\r &nbsp;'),(11,33,'d','en_us','07.02.02','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/02-Contacts/ContactsHome.html','Suppliers.Contacts','Suppliers - Contacts','Suppliers - Contacts\r \r \r \r \r Suppliers - Contacts \r Supplier contacts contain information about your suppliers of inventory, services and other purchases required for your business. The procedures to setup, edit and delete supplier contacts is similar to that for customers within KSSBooks. \r Supplier Account features:\r \r   Default global settings for purchase account and terms; customizable  for each individual supplier\r   Unlimited billing addresses\r   Unlimited shipping addresses\r    Individaul purchase rep default assignment \r   Freee-form notes field \r \r Related Topics\r Suppliers\r Entering a new supplier \r Updating supplier information\r Deleting a supplier \r Setting supplier payment terms and credit limits \r Purchase  Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r   Deleting a purchase order\r   Closing a purchase order\r Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r   Receiving inventory directly from a supplier\r Other Supplier Actions \r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r   Writing a check to a supplier\r   Issuing a supplier credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking supplier balance\r &nbsp;'),(12,17,'d','en_us','07.02.03.01','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/03-PurchaseOrders/01-EnterPO.html','Purchase Orders.Entering','Entering Customer Purchase Orders','Entering Customer Purchase Orders\r \r \r \r \r  Entering Supplier Purchase Orders\r Purchase orders are used to enter purchase from a supplier. Reports can be generated to list the inventory shortfalls and inventory purchases. Each inventory item has a minimum balance field that can be used to help identify when inventory needs to be ordered. Purchase orders do not affect your financial situation, income statement or balance sheet. they merely act as a placeholder to determine inventory stock levels needed to add or replace inventory stock levels. \r \r   From the Suppliers Menu, select Purchase Orders. The Purchase Order form will load.\r   Enter the Supplier ID and click on the open icon right of the Supplier ID window. The supplier popup window will appear. Select the supplier from the list and the information will be pre-loaded into the Purchase Order form.\r     \r     NOTE: The Supplier ID text box also acts as a search box to quickly find suppliers.\r     \r     Supplier records consist of a main address, billing addresses and shipping addresses. Select the billing address and shipping address from the pull down menus. New addresses may be added to either the shipping or billing address if they cannot be found from either of the menus. Selecting the add/update button will update the database whereas leaving it unchecked will just retain the address for this purchase order.\r     Drop Ship - If this is a drop ship, select the Drop Ship box and the drop ship search box will appear. Customers can be searched and their shipping information will be entered into the drop down or the shipping address may be entered directly into the address fields. \r   Enter the purchase order Post Date and expected Receipt Date. Popup calendars are provided to help with the selection.\r    Purchase Order Number - Enter the purchase order number. If left blank, the next sequential purchase order number will be automatically generated by the system.\r    Enter the your purchase reference   number, store id and purchase representative. The default accounts payable account is loaded and can be changed. The supplier payment terms are loaded when a supplier is selected from the supplier popup. If a new supplier is entered, the default payment terms are loaded. To change the payment terms, click on the icon next to the terms text field and the terms popup will be displayed. Select the terms for this purchase order and press Save to enter the terms into the purchase order form.\r   Enter the inventory items for the purchase order. The form defaults with a single inventory line but more may be added by pressing the Add button located in the lower left area of the purchase order form. Enter the quantity requested. The item cost value assigned to the sku will be placed in the price field and the line total will be calculated. \r     \r     NOTE: The inventory SKU field also acts as a search field for the inventory popup. To quickly find an inventory item, enter part of the item sku or description and press the icon next to the SKU. The SKU, description and pricing fields will be filled in. \r     \r   Enter the inventory SKU, description and price (or retrieve from the inventory popup) for the line item. Enter more line items as necessary. \r   Enter the shipping charges (or use the shipping estimator to calculate freight charges).\r   Select  the tax authority, the tax will be automatically calculated.\r   Save or Print the purchase order. Error checking will be performed and any errors will be indicated either in a popup for errors before the form is submitted or at the top of the reloaded page (for errors during  processing). If the Purchase Order number field was left blank, a number will be assigned by the system. If the Print button was selected, the purchase order will be posted first followed by a popup window displaying the possible forms to print, select the form to print and press the Print button. \r \r Related Topics\r Supplier Accounts\r Entering a new supplier \r     Editing a supplier account \r     Deleting a supplier account\r     Setting supplier payment terms and credit limits \r Purchase Orders\r     Editing a purchase order\r     Deleting a purchase order\r     Closing a purchase order\r     Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r     Receiving inventory directly from a supplier\r Other Supplier Actions \r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r   Writing a check to a supplier.\r   Issuing a supplier credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking supplier balances\r Tax Authorities \r Setting up tax authorities\r    Setting up tax rates\r Shipping Estimator\r Setting up the shipping estimator'),(13,17,'d','en_us','07.02.03.02','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/03-PurchaseOrders/02-EditPO.html','Purchase Orders.Editing','Editing a Supplier Purchase Order','Editing a Supplier Purchase Order\r \r \r \r \r Editing a Supplier Purchase Order\r Purchase  orders can only be edited if no items have been received from the purchase order. If any items have been received, the corresponding purchase/receipt must be removed before the purchase order can be edited. In this case, the purchase order should be closed. See Closing a Purchase Order. Closing a purchase order will remove all remaining \'quantity on  order\' quantities from inventory. \r \r   From the Suppliers Menu, select Purchase Orders. The Purchase Order form will load. \r   Press the Open button and a popup will appear listing the purchase orders for the current period. Select the sales order to be edited and the sales order form will be filled in. \r     \r     NOTE: Use the period pull down and search box to facilitate locating the desired purchase order. \r   \r   Make any necessary changes. Item rows may not be changed if some or all have been received.\r   Press the Save button to save the changes.\r \r When a purchase order is saves, the journal entry is re-posted to the database and the quantity on  order values are readjusted. This action will not affect the income statement or balance sheet since a purchase order represents an allocation of inventory and not an actual purchase (monetary transaction).\r Related Topics\r Supplier Accounts\r Entering a new supplier \r     Editing a supplier account \r     Deleting a supplier account\r     Setting supplier payment terms and credit limits \r Purchase Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r     Deleting a purchase order\r     Closing a purchase order\r     Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r     Receiving inventory directly from a supplier\r Other Supplier Actions \r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r  Writing a check to a supplier\r   Issuing a supplier credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking supplier balances\r Tax Authorities \r Setting up tax authorities\r    Setting up tax rates\r Shipping Estimator\r Setting up the shipping estimator'),(14,17,'d','en_us','07.02.03.03','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/03-PurchaseOrders/03-DeletePO.html','Purchase Orders.Deleting','Deleting a Customer Purchase Order','Deleting a Customer Purchase Order\r \r \r \r \r  Deleting a Supplier Purchase Order\r Purchase  orders can only be deleted if no items have been received from the purchase order. If any items have been received, the corresponding purchase/receipt must be removed before the purchase order can be deleted. In this case, the purchase order should be closed. See Closing a Purchase Order. Closing a purchase order will remove all remaining \'quantity on  order\' quantities from inventory. \r \r   From the Suppliers Menu, select Purchase Orders. The Purchase Order form will load. \r   Press the Open button and a popup will appear listing the purchase orders for the current period. Select the sales order to be deleted and the sales order form will be filled in. \r     \r     NOTE: Use the period pull down and search box to facilitate locating the desired purchase order. \r   \r   Press the Delete button and confirm the action on the confirmation popup.\r \r When a purchase order is deleted, the journal entry is removed from the database and the quantity on  order values are readjusted. This action will not affect the income statement or balance sheet since a purchase order represents an allocation of inventory and not an actual purchase (monetary transaction).\r Related Topics\r Supplier Accounts\r Entering a new supplier \r     Editing a supplier account \r     Deleting a supplier account\r     Setting supplier payment terms and credit limits \r Purchase Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r     Editing a purchase order\r     Closing a purchase order\r     Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r     Receiving inventory directly from a supplier\r Other Supplier Actions \r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r   Writing a check to a supplier\r   Issuing a supplier credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking supplier balances'),(15,17,'d','en_us','07.02.03.04','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/03-PurchaseOrders/04-POManager.html','Purchase Orders.PO Manager','Purchase Order Manager','Purchase Order Manager\r \r \r \r \r Purchase Order Manager\r The purchase order manager lists all open purchase orders in the current accounting period. From this screen, the purchase order may be reviewed, inventory items may be received, and item delivery dates may be entered. The search period pull-down menu and the text search box are available to quickly locate purchase orders.\r Viewing a Purchase Order\r \r   Select Suppliers-&gt;Purchase Order Manager\r   Locate the purchase order to view and press the button labeled View.\r   The Purchase Order screen will load and the form will be filled in with the information of the selected PO.\r   From here, the purchase order may be edited, deleted,  closed or reviewed. \r \r Receiving Inventory from a Purchase Order\r \r   Select Suppliers-&gt;Purchase Order Manager \r   Locate the purchase order to receive against and press the button labeled \'Receive\'.\r   The Purchase/Receive screen will load and the remaining items from the selected PO will be shown.\r   Receive in the quantities received for each line item.\r    Make any other changes as necessary; such as the suppliers invoice number or check the Waiting for Invoice if the invoice has not been received.\r   Press the Save icon to save the inventory receipt.\r \r Changing Delivery Dates for a Purchase Order\r When a purchase order is placed, the expected delivery date is set based on the  Lead Time field specific to the inventory item. After a PO is sent to a supplier, the suppliers delivery dates may not align with the items Lead Time date. the estimated delivery dates may be modified here to reflect the current estimated delivery dates for each line item on the PO. the delivery dates field is useful to identify when items are expected for filling back-orders and notifications of expected arrivals of inventory items.\r \r    Select Suppliers-&gt;Purchase Order Manager \r   Locate the purchase order to adjust or view the expected delivery dates and press the button labeled \'Delivery Dates\'.\r   A popup will appear listing each line item from the PO, the quantity ordered and the description. The currently expected delivery date will also be displayed.\r   If necessary, enter a new delivery date for each item on the PO. A popup calendar is provided to help locate dates. If no change is necessary, leave the date field blank to retain the current delivery date. \r   After updating all affected delivery dates, press the Save icon the save the changes and return to the Purchase Order Manager window. \r \r Related Topics\r Supplier Accounts\r Entering a new supplier \r     Editing a supplier account \r     Deleting a supplier account\r     Setting supplier payment terms and credit limits \r Purchase Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r     Editing a purchase order\r     Deleting a purchase order\r     Closing a purchase order\r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r     Receiving inventory directly from a supplier\r Reports and Forms \r Open purchase order report'),(16,17,'d','en_us','07.02.03.05','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/03-PurchaseOrders/05-ClosePO.html','Purchase Orders.CLosing','Closing a Supplier Purchase Order','Closing a Supplier Purchase Order\r \r \r \r \r Closing a Supplier Purchase Order\r Purchase  orders can  be closed for several reasons. They may be closed directly from the Edit PO screen by selecting the close button.Closed POs will not affect the inventory levels or appear in any inventory stock level calculations. POs may also be closed by KSSBooks if all the items have been received through the Purchase/Receive screen. Closing a purchase order will remove all remaining \'quantity on  order\' quantities from inventory identified in the purchase order being closed that have not been received. \r \r   From the Suppliers Menu, select Purchase Orders. The Purchase Order form will load. \r   Press the Open button and a popup will appear listing the purchase orders for the current period. Select the sales order to be closed and the sales order form will be filled in. \r     \r     NOTE: Use the period pull down and search box to facilitate locating the desired purchase order. \r   \r   Check the Close selection box.\r   Press the Save button.\r \r When a purchase order is closed, the  quantity on  order values are readjusted. This action will not affect the income statement or balance sheet since a purchase order represents an allocation of inventory and not an actual purchase (monetary transaction).\r Related Topics\r Supplier Accounts\r Entering a new supplier \r     Editing a supplier account \r     Deleting a supplier account\r     Setting supplier payment terms and credit limits \r Purchase Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r     Editing a purchase order\r     Deleting a purchase order\r     Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r &nbsp;'),(17,33,'0','en_us','07.02.03','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/03-PurchaseOrders/POHome.html','Suppliers.Purchase Orders','Suppliers - Purchase Orders','Suppliers - Purchase Orders\r \r \r \r \r Suppliers - Purchase Orders\r Purchase orders are used to enter inventory and services purchased from a supplier. Reports can be generated to list the inventory shortfalls and inventory purchases. Each inventory item has a minimum balance field that can be used to help identify when inventory needs to be ordered. Purchase orders do not affect your financial situation, income statement or balance sheet. they merely act as a placeholder to determine inventory stock levels needed to add or replace inventory stock levels. \r Purchase Order features:\r \r   Multiple inventory line items \r   Separate billing and shipping address \r   Drop ship ability \r    Individual general ledger accounts for each line item\r   Freight estimator to calculate shipping costs\r   Sales tax can be added to PO \r   Customizable payment terms\r \r Related Topics\r Supplier Accounts\r Entering a new supplier \r   Editing a supplier account \r   Deleting a  supplier account\r Setting supplier payment terms and credit limits \r Purchase Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r    Editing a purchase order\r   Deleting a purchase order\r   Closing a purchase order\r   Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r     Receiving inventory directly from a supplier\r Other Supplier Actions \r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r Writing a check to a supplier\r     Issuing a supplier credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking supplier balances\r &nbsp;'),(18,21,'d','en_us','07.02.04.01','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/04-Quotes/01-EnterQuote.html','Supplier Request for Quote.Entering','Entering Supplier Request for Quote','Entering Supplier Request for Quote\r \r \r \r \r  Entering Supplier Request for Quote\r Request for Quote are used to enter purchase from a supplier. Reports can be generated to list the inventory shortfalls and inventory purchases. Each inventory item has a minimum balance field that can be used to help identify when inventory needs to be ordered. Request for Quotes do not affect your financial situation, income statement or balance sheet. they merely act as a placeholder to determine inventory stock levels needed to add or replace inventory stock levels. \r \r   From the Suppliers Menu, select Request for Quote. The request for quote form will load.\r   Enter the Supplier ID and click on the open icon right of the Supplier ID window. The supplier popup window will appear. Select the supplier from the list and the information will be pre-loaded into the request for quote form.\r     \r     NOTE: The Supplier ID text box also acts as a search box to quickly find suppliers.\r     \r     Supplier records consist of a main address, billing addresses and shipping addresses. Select the billing address and shipping address from the pull down menus. New addresses may be added to either the shipping or billing address if they cannot be found from either of the menus. Selecting the add/update button will update the database whereas leaving it unchecked will just retain the address for this request for quote.\r     Drop Ship - If this is a drop ship, select the Drop Ship box and the drop ship search box will appear. Customers can be searched and their shipping information will be entered into the drop down or the shipping address may be entered directly into the address fields. \r   Enter the request for quote Post Date and expected Receipt Date. Popup calendars are provided to help with the selection.\r    request for quote Number - Enter the request for quote number. If left blank, the next sequential request for quote number will be automatically generated by the system.\r    Enter the your purchase reference   number, store id and purchase representative. The default accounts payable account is loaded and can be changed. The supplier payment terms are loaded when a supplier is selected from the supplier popup. If a new supplier is entered, the default payment terms are loaded. To change the payment terms, click on the icon next to the terms text field and the terms popup will be displayed. Select the terms for this request for quote and press Save to enter the terms into the request for quote form.\r   Enter the inventory items for the request for quote. The form defaults with a single inventory line but more may be added by pressing the Add button located in the lower left area of the request for quote form. Enter the quantity requested. The item cost value assigned to the sku will be placed in the price field and the line total will be calculated. \r     \r     NOTE: The inventory SKU field also acts as a search field for the inventory popup. To quickly find an inventory item, enter part of the item sku or description and press the icon next to the SKU. The SKU, description and pricing fields will be filled in. \r     \r   Enter the inventory SKU, description and price (or retrieve from the inventory popup) for the line item. Enter more line items as necessary. \r   Enter the shipping charges (or use the shipping estimator to calculate freight charges).\r   Select  the tax authority, the tax will be automatically calculated.\r   Save or Print the request for quote. Error checking will be performed and any errors will be indicated either in a popup for errors before the form is submitted or at the top of the reloaded page (for errors during  processing). If the request for quote number field was left blank, a number will be assigned by the system. If the Print button was selected, the request for quote will be posted first followed by a popup window displaying the possible forms to print, select the form to print and press the Print button. \r \r Related Topics\r Supplier Accounts\r Entering a new supplier \r     Updating supplier information\r     Setting supplier payment terms and credit limits \r Supplier Request for Quote\r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r     Editing a request for quote\r     Deleting a request for quote  \r Purchase Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r     Editing a purchase order\r     Deleting a purchase order\r     Closing a purchase order\r     Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r     Receiving inventory directly from a supplier\r Other Supplier Actions \r   Writing a check to a supplier\r     Issuing a supplier credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking supplier balances\r Tax Authorities \r Setting up tax authorities\r    Setting up tax rates'),(19,21,'d','en_us','07.02.04.02','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/04-Quotes/02-EditQuote.html','Supplier Request for Quote.Editing','Editing a Supplier Request for Quote','Editing a Supplier Request for Quote\r \r \r \r \r  Editing a Supplier Request for Quote\r Supplier purchase  quotes can only be deleted if no items have been received from the request for quote. If any items have been received, the corresponding purchase/receipt must be removed before the request for quote can be deleted. In this case, the request for quote should be closed. See Closing a request for quote. Closing a request for quote will remove all remaining \'quantity on  order\' quantities from inventory. \r \r   From the Suppliers Menu, select Request for Quote. The request for quote form will load. \r   Press the Open button and a popup will appear listing the Request for Quotes for the current period. Select the sales order to be deleted and the sales order form will be filled in. \r     \r     NOTE: Use the period pull down and search box to facilitate locating the desired request for quote. \r   \r   Press the Delete button and confirm the action on the confirmation popup.\r \r When a request for quote is deleted, the journal entry is removed from the database and the quantity on  order values are readjusted. This action will not affect the income statement or balance sheet since a request for quote represents an allocation of inventory and not an actual purchase (monetary transaction).\r Related Topics\r Supplier Accounts\r Entering a new supplier \r     Updating supplier information\r     Setting supplier payment terms and credit limits \r Supplier Request for Quote\r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r     Editing a request for quote\r     Deleting a request for quote  \r Purchase Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r     Editing a purchase order\r     Deleting a purchase order\r     Closing a purchase order\r     Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r     Receiving inventory directly from a supplier\r Other Supplier Actions \r  Writing a check to a supplier\r     Issuing a supplier credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking supplier balances\r &nbsp;'),(20,21,'d','en_us','07.02.04.03','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/04-Quotes/03-DeleteQuote.html','Supplier Request for Quote.Deleting','Deleting a Supplier Request for Quote','Deleting a Supplier Request for Quote\r \r \r \r \r  Deleting a Supplier Request for Quote\r Purchase  quotes can only be deleted if no items have been received from the request for quote. If any items have been received, the corresponding purchase/receipt must be removed before the request for quote can be deleted. In this case, the request for quote should be closed. See Closing a request for quote. Closing a request for quote will remove all remaining \'quantity on  order\' quantities from inventory. \r \r   From the Suppliers Menu, select Request for Quote. The request for quote form will load. \r   Press the Open button and a popup will appear listing the Request for Quotes for the current period. Select the sales order to be deleted and the sales order form will be filled in. \r     \r     NOTE: Use the period pull down and search box to facilitate locating the desired request for quote. \r   \r   Press the Delete button and confirm the action on the comfirmation popup.\r \r When a request for quote is deleted, the journal entry is removed from the database and the quantity on  order values are readjusted. This action will not affect the income statement or balance sheet since a request for quote represents an allocation of inventory and not an actual purchase (monetary transaction).\r Related Topics\r Supplier Accounts\r Entering a new supplier \r     Updating supplier information\r     Setting supplier payment terms and credit limits \r Supplier Request for Quote\r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r     Editing a request for quote\r     Deleting a request for quote  \r Purchase Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r     Editing a purchase order\r     Deleting a purchase order\r     Closing a purchase order\r     Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r     Receiving inventory directly from a supplier\r Other Supplier Actions \r   Writing a check to a supplier\r     Issuing a supplier credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking supplier balances\r &nbsp;'),(21,33,'0','en_us','07.02.04','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/04-Quotes/QuotesHome.html','Suppliers.Request for Quotes','Suppliers - Request for Quotes','Suppliers - Request for Quotes\r \r \r \r \r Suppliers - Request for Quotes\r Request for Quote are used to enter purchase from a supplier. Reports can be generated to list the inventory shortfalls and inventory purchases. Each inventory item has a minimum balance field that can be used to help identify when inventory needs to be ordered. Request for Quotes do not affect your financial situation, income statement or balance sheet. they merely act as a placeholder to determine inventory stock levels needed to add or replace inventory stock levels. \r Supplier Request for Quote features:\r \r   Multiple inventory line items \r   Separate billing and shipping address \r   Drop ship ability \r    Individual general ledger accounts for each line item\r   Freight estimator to calculate shipping costs\r   Sales tax can be added to PO \r   Customizable payment terms\r \r Related Topics\r Supplier Accounts\r Entering a new supplier \r     Updating supplier information\r     Setting supplier payment terms and credit limits \r Supplier Request for Quote\r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r   Editing a request for quote\r   Deleting a request for quote \r \r Purchase Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r     Editing a purchase order\r     Deleting a purchase order\r     Closing a purchase order\r     Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r     Receiving inventory directly from a supplier\r Other Supplier Actions \r   Writing a check to a supplier\r   Issuing a supplier credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking supplier balances\r &nbsp;'),(22,24,'d','en_us','07.02.05.01','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/05-Purchases/01-ReceivePO.html','Suppliers.Receipts from a PO','Receive Inventory from a Purchase Order','Receive Inventory from a Purchase Order\r \r \r \r \r Receive Inventory from a Purchase Order \r Supplier purchases are represented as inventory items, services and other bills received related to operating your company. Purchases affect the financial picture of your company. All purchase records are maintained in the purchase/receive journal. \r Related Topics\r Suppliers\r Entering a purchase order\r   Receiving inventory directly from suppliers\r   Editing a purchase/receive\r   Deleting a purchase/receive \r Inventory\r Entering inventory items \r Banking\r Paying a bill - Checks, EFTs to you suppliers and service providers.\r Writing a check to a supplier.\r Related Reports\r Checking inventory balances\r   Checking supplier account balances\r &nbsp;'),(23,24,'d','en_us','07.02.05.02','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/05-Purchases/02-ReceiveInv.html','Suppliers.Receipts from a supplier','Receive Inventory Directly from a Supplier','Receive Inventory Directly from a Supplier\r \r \r \r \r Receive Inventory Directly from a Supplier\r Inventory can be received directly form a supplier without a purchase order against the supplier account. \r &nbsp;\r Related Topics\r Suppliers\r Entering a purchase order\r   Receiving inventory from a purchase order \r   Editing a purchase/receive\r   Deleting a purchase/receive \r Inventory\r Entering inventory items \r Banking\r Paying a bill - Checks, EFTs to you suppliers and service providers.\r Writing a check to a supplier.\r Related Reports\r Checking inventory balances\r   Checking supplier account balances\r &nbsp;'),(24,33,'0','en_us','07.02.05','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/05-Purchases/PurchasesHome.html','Suppliers.Purchases','Suppliers - Purchases','Suppliers - Purchases\r \r \r \r \r Suppliers - Purchase/Receive\r Supplier purchases are represented as inventory items, services and other bills received related to operating your company. Purchases affect the financial picture of your company. All purchase records are maintained in the purchase/receive journal. \r Related Topics\r Suppliers\r Entering a purchase order\r    Receiving inventory from a purchase order \r    Receiving inventory directly from suppliers\r   Editing a purchase/receive\r   Deleting a purchase/receive \r   Checking supplier balances \r Inventory\r Adding inventory items\r Banking\r Paying a bill - Checks, EFTs to you suppliers and service providers.\r Writing a check to a supplier.\r Reports\r Checking inventory balances\r   Supplier history report\r \r &nbsp;'),(25,33,'d','en_us','07.02.06','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/06-POP/POPHome.html','Suppliers.Point of Purchase','Suppliers - Point of Purchase','Suppliers - Point of Purchase\r \r \r \r \r Suppliers - Point of Purchase\r Point of purchase is the process of receiving an item and applying a payment at the time of acquisition.'),(26,33,'d','en_us','07.02.06','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/06-Payments/PaymentsHome.html','Suppliers.Payments','Suppliers - Payments','Suppliers - Payments\r \r \r \r \r Suppliers - Payments\r Paying a supplier for products purchased.'),(27,30,'d','en_us','07.02.07.01','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/07-CreditMemos/01-EnterCrdMemo.html','Supplier Credit Memo.Entering','Entering Supplier Credit Memo','Entering Supplier Credit Memo\r \r \r \r \r  Entering Supplier Credit Memos\r Credit Memos are used to enter sales to a supplier. Once a credit memo has been entered several events may then occur. Inventory items can be ordered (Purchase Orders), items shipped or drop-shipped, pick slips, packing slips or credit memos can be generated for some or all of the items in the order as they become available in your inventory. Reports can be generated to list the inventory shortfalls inventory sales. Credit Memos do not affect your financial situation, income statement or balance sheet. they merely act as a placeholder to determine inventory stock levels needed to fulfill sales. \r \r   From the Suppliers Menu, select Credit Memos. The Credit Memo form will load.\r   Enter the Supplier ID and click on the open icon right of the Supplier ID window. The supplier popup window will appear. Select the supplier from the list and the information will be pre-loaded into the Credit Memo form.\r     \r     NOTE: The Supplier ID text box also acts as a search box to quickly find suppliers.\r     \r     Supplier records consist of a main address, billing addresses and shipping addresses. Select the billing address and shipping address from the pull down menus. New addresses may be added to either the shipping or billing address if they cannot be found from either of the menus. Selecting the add/update button will update the database whereas leaving it unchecked will just retain the address for this credit memo.\r     Drop Ship - If this is a drop ship, select the Drop Ship box and the drop ship search box will appear. Suppliers can be searched and their shipping information will be entered into the drop down or the shipping address may be entered directly into the address fields. \r   Enter the credit memo Post Date and expected Ship Date. Popup calendars will help with the selection.\r    Credit Memo Number - Enter the credit memo number. If left blank, the next credit memo number will be automatically generated by the system.\r    Enter the suppliers purchase order number, store id and sales representative. The default accounts receivable account is loaded and can be changed. The supplier payment terms are loaded when a supplier is selected from the supplier popup. If a new supplier is entered, the default payment terms are loaded. To change the payment terms, click on the icon next to the terms text field and the terms popup will be displayed. Select the terms for this credit memo and press Save to enter the terms into the credit memo form.\r   Enter the inventory items for the credit memo. The form defaults with a single inventory line but more may be added by pressing the Add button located in the lower left area of the credit memo form. Enter the quantity requested.\r     \r     NOTE: The inventory SKU field also acts as a search field for the inventory popup. To quickly find an inventory item, enter part of the item sku or description and press the icon next to the SKU. The SKU, description and pricing fields will be filled in. \r     \r   Enter the inventory SKU, description and price (or retrieve from the inventory popup) for the line item. Enter more line items as necessary. \r   Enter the shipping charges (or use the shipping estimator to calculate freight charges).\r   Select  the tax authority, the tax will be automatically calculated.\r   Save or Print the credit memo. Error checking will be performed and any errors will be indicated either in a popup for errors before the form is submitted or at the top of the reloaded page (for errors during  processing). If the Purchase Order number field was left blank, a number will be assigned by the system. If the Print button was selected, the credit memo will be posted first followed by a popup window displaying the possible forms to print, select the form to print and press the Print button. \r \r Related Topics\r Suppliers\r Entering a new supplier \r Updating supplier information\r Setting supplier payment terms and credit limits \r Checking supplier balances \r Tax Authorities \r Setting up tax authorities\r    Setting up tax rates\r Shipping Estimator\r Setting up the shipping estimator\r Credit Memos\r Edit a supplier credit memo (VCM)\r   Delete a supplier credit memo (VCM)\r Receiving a credit memo\r Reports\r Printing a credit memo'),(28,30,'d','en_us','07.02.07.02','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/07-CreditMemos/02-EditCrdMemo.html','Supplier Credit Memo.Editing','Editing a Supplier Credit Memo','Editing a Supplier Credit Memo\r \r \r \r \r Editing a Supplier Credit Memo\r Editing an invoice can be performed at any time.\r \r   From the Suppliers Menu, select Credit Memos. The Credit Memo form will load. \r   Press the Open button and a popup will appear listing the Credit Memos for the current period. Select the credit memo to be edited and the credit memo form will be filled in. \r     \r     NOTE: Use the period pull down and search box to facilitate locating the desired credit memo. \r   \r   Enter any changes, as needed, to the credit memo. If any line items from the credit memo have been shipped, that particular line item cannot be deleted or the SKU changed.\r   Press the Save button and confirm the action on the confirmation popup.\r \r When an credit memo is edited, the journal entry is re-posted in the database and the quantity on hand values are readjusted. This action will  affect the income statement and balance sheet since a invoice represents an actual sale (monetary transaction).\r Related Topics\r Suppliers\r Entering a new supplier \r Updating supplier information\r Setting supplier payment terms and credit limits \r Checking supplier balances \r Tax Authorities \r Setting up tax authorities\r    Setting up tax rates\r Shipping Estimator\r Setting up the shipping estimator\r   Shipping an invoice\r Credit Memos \r Enter a supplier credit memo (VCM)\r    Delete a supplier credit memo (VCM)'),(29,30,'d','en_us','07.02.07.03','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/07-CreditMemos/03-DeleteCrdMemo.html','Supplier Credit Memo.Deleting','Deleting a Supplier Credit Memo','Deleting a Supplier Credit Memo\r \r \r \r \r  Deleting a Supplier Credit Memo\r Sales orders can only be deleted if no items have been shipped from the invoice. If any items have been shipped, the corresponding invoice/sale must be removed before the invoice can be deleted. In this case, the invoice should be closed. See Closing a Credit Memo. Closing a invoice will remove all remaining \'quantity on invoice\' quantities from inventory. \r \r   From the Suppliers Menu, select Credit Memos. The Credit Memo form will load. \r   Press the Open button and a popup will appear listing the credit memos for the current period. Select the credit memo to be deleted and the credit memo form will be filled in. \r     \r     NOTE: Use the period pull down and search box to facilitate locating the desired credit memo. \r   \r   Press the Delete button and confirm the action on the confirmation popup.\r \r When an credit memo is edited, the journal entry is removed from the database and the quantity on hand values are readjusted. This action will affect the income statement and balance sheet since a credit memo represents an actual sale (monetary transaction).\r Related Topics\r Credit Memos\r  Enter a supplier credit memo (VCM) \r     Edit a supplier credit memo (VCM)\r Closing a credit memo'),(30,33,'0','en_us','07.02.07','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/07-CreditMemos/CreditsHome.html','Suppliers.Credit Memos','Suppliers - Credit Memos','Suppliers - Credit Memos\r \r \r \r \r Suppliers - Credit Memos\r  Enter a supplier credit memo (VCM) \r   Edit a supplier credit memo (VCM)\r   Delete a supplier credit memo (VCM)\r &nbsp;'),(31,33,'d','en_us','07.02.08','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/08-Status/StatusHome.html','Suppliers.Status','Suppliers - Status','Suppliers - Status\r \r \r \r \r Suppliers - Status\r Status of the supplier account.'),(32,33,'d','en_us','07.02.09','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/09-POP/POPHome.html','Suppliers.Point of Purchase','Suppliers - Point of Purchase','Suppliers - Point of Purchase\r \r \r \r \r Suppliers - Point of Purchase\r Point of purchase is the process of receiving an item and applying a payment at the time of acquisition.'),(33,175,'0','en_us','07.02','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Suppliers/SupplierHome.html','Suppliers','Suppliers Home','Suppliers Home\r \r \r \r \r Suppliers Home\r Suppliers are your suppliers of products and services.  They are used in KSSBooks to represent people or companies that payments are made to.  This will include suppliers of your inventory items, governmental organizations for tax payments, services provided to your company (shipping companies, payroll, utilities, professional services, etc) and other expense related accounts.  Generally, suppliers include anyone that you make payments to.\r KSSBooks uses a single database table to hold employee, Warehouse, supplier and customer account information. \r Supplier account features include:\r \r   Fields for main account address along with unlimited Warehouse billing addresses and shipping addresses.\r   Default general ledger settings for purchases\r   2 main telephone numbers, 1 fax number, email and website fields\r   Customer account number\r   Government ID (FEIN) Number\r   Discount and Payment terms specific to an account\r \r Security Settings\r Related Topics:\r Supplier Accounts\r Entering a supplier account\r   Deleting a supplier account\r   Editing a supplier account\r   Setting default payment terms \r   Adding Warehouse and shipping addresses\r Supplier Quotes \r  Enter a supplier Request for Quote  (RFQ) \r   Edit a supplier Request for Quote (RFQ)\r   Delete a supplier Request for Quote\r   (RFQ)\r   Convert a request for quote to a Purchase Order\r Purchase Orders\r  Enter a supplier purchase order (PO) \r   Edit a supplier purchase order (PO)\r   Delete a supplier purchase order (PO)\r   Receive inventory from a purchase order (PO Manager)\r Supplier Purchases and Payments \r Receive inventory\r  Paying a bill - Checks, EFTs to you suppliers and service providers.\r  Receiving inventory from a supplier \r Payments by credit card \r Supplier Credit Memos\r  Enter a supplier credit memo (VCM) \r   Edit a supplier credit memo (VCM)\r   Delete a supplier credit memo (VCM)\r Reports and Forms \r Standard supplier reports\r   Standard supplier forms\r &nbsp;'),(34,66,'d','en_us','07.03.01','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/01-General/GeneralHome.html','Customers.General Information','Customers - General Information','Customers - General Information     Customers - General Information This section covers the activites realted to your customers. Accounts -  Sales Orders -  Sales Quotes -  Sales/Invoices -  Point Of Sale -  Credit Memos -  Customer  Status -'),(35,39,'d','en_us','07.03.02.01','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/02-Accounts/01-NewAccount.html','Customer Accounts.Entering','Entering a Customer Account','Entering a Customer Account\r \r \r \r \r  Entering a Customer Account \r Customer accounts include any outside organization that you sell goods or services to. Generally, they are organizations that you receive payments from. \r NOTE: Customer accounts may be created at time of sale by entering the required information and checking the Add/Update button in the Sales/Invoice, Receipt or Sales Order form. In this case, an unique account ID must be entered and the account will be created using the standard terms, default Sales GL account. No User ID, Account Number, Federal ID number, or additional shipping or billing addresses will be created with the add/update feature. \r To create a new account:\r \r   Select Customers-&gt;New Customer or Select the New icon form the Customers-&gt;Maintain Customers page.\r    Enter an unique Customer ID. The Customer ID (or short name) is an unique field to identify this customer form all other customers. Maximum length is 20 characters.\r   Enter remaining Primary Contact and Main Mailing (invoicing) Address information.  Required fields are identified by a (*).\r   Enter the default sales account. This is typically an accounts receivable general ledger account type.\r   Enter an user id assigned to this customer. \r   Enter your account number with this customer. This number can be used for sales orders, invoices to reference their account to the customer.\r    Enter the Tax or Federal ID number. generally used for tax purposes.\r    If the customer will be shipping to multiple locations, additional ship to addresses can be added in the Shipping Addresses form area. Unlimited shipping addresses may be assigned to a customer but only one may be added at a time.\r   Enter the payment terms you have with the customer. The defaults are preloaded but may be over-ridden on a customer by customer basis. \r   If the customer has additional remit to (invoicing) addresses, they may be added in the Billing Addresses form area. Unlimited billing addresses may be assigned to a customer but only one may be added at a time. \r   Press the Save icon and the record will be saved and you will be returned to the Maintain Customers page. \r \r Related Topics\r Customers\r   Updating a customer account\r   Deleting a customer account\r   Setting up a customer credit limit\r Sales Orders\r Deleting a sales order\r   Closing a sales order\r Sales/Invoice\r Selling items from a Sales Order \r Reports and Forms \r Checking customer balances\r &nbsp;'),(36,39,'d','en_us','07.03.02.02','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/02-Accounts/02-EditAccount.html','Customer Account.Editing','Editing a Customer Account','Editing a Customer Account\r \r \r \r \r Editing a Customer Account \r To edit a customer record:\r \r   Select Customers-&gt;Maintain Customers page.\r   Select the Edit icon next to the customer to edit. A search box has been provided to quickly locate the customer.\r   Edit/update/change any fields for the customer.\r   Add/Delete any additional shipping or billing addresses.\r   Press the Save button to save the changes. You will be returned to the Maintain Customers page. \r \r Related Topics\r Customers\r  Adding a new customer account \r   Deleting a customer account \r   Setting up a customer credit limit\r Checking customer balances \r Sales Orders\r Entering  a sales order\r   Deleting a sales order\r   Closing a sales order\r &nbsp;'),(37,39,'d','en_us','07.03.02.03','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/02-Accounts/03-DeleteAccount.html','Customer Account.Deleting','Deleting a Customer Account','Deleting a Customer Account\r \r \r \r \r  Deleting a Customer Account \r NOTE: Customers cannot be deleted if they have a journal entry associated with them. \r To delete a customer record:\r \r   Select Customers-&gt;Maintain Customers page.\r   Select the Delete icon next to the customer to delete. A search box has been provided to quickly locate the customer.\r   Confirm the deletion and you will be returned to the Maintain Customers page. \r \r Related Topics\r Customers\r  Adding a new customer account \r   Editing a customer account \r Sales Orders\r   Deleting a sales order\r   Closing a sales order\r &nbsp;'),(38,39,'d','en_us','07.03.02.04','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/02-Accounts/04-PaymentTerms.html','Customer Accounts.Payment Terms','Customer Payment Terms','Customer Payment Terms\r \r \r \r \r Customer Payment Terms\r Customer payment terms may be set up through the configuration screen. The terms set up will be applied as the default terms for all new customer account.  Additionally, existing accounts with out terms defined (or \'Use Standard Terms\') will track the terms defined in the configuration setup definitions. Individual customer terms may also be set up for customers whose terms are different from the standard terms. Terms may also be set up for specific sales through the Sales Order/Invoice procedure. \r Setting up Default Terms \r \r   Select Company-&gt;Customer Defaults.\r   Edit the fields as necessary. The terms type defaults to the standard X% discount in Y days, Net Z days.\r   Set the default customer credit limit to use. \r \r Setting up Customer Specific Payment Terms\r \r    Select Customers-&gt;Maintain Customers. \r   Search for the customer whose terms you want to change and press the edit icon to reach the detailed page.\r    Under the section titled Payment Terms, check the radio button for the terms type to apply to this customer.\r   Depending on the terms type selected, the Discount, Due In, Net and date fields will be active. Fill in the fields for the terms type selected.\r   Enter the credit limit for the current customer.\r   Press the Save icon to save the changes.\r \r Setting Payment Terms for a Single Purchase\r \r   Select Customers-&gt;Sales/Invoice (or Sales Order, Customer Quote).\r   On the form select the Open icon next to the terms field. A popup window will open with the current terms selected.\r   Change the terms as necessary and press Save to enter the new terms into the form.\r \r Related Topics\r Customers\r  Adding a new customer account\r   Editing a customer account\r Sales Orders\r  Deleting a sales order\r   Closing a sales order\r Reports and Forms \r Checking customer balances\r &nbsp;'),(39,66,'0','en_us','07.03.02','modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/02-Accounts/AccountsHome.html','Customers.Customer Accounts','Customers - Customer Accounts','Customers - Customer Accounts\r \r \r \r \r Customers -  Accounts\r Customer accounts contain information about your customers of your business. The procedures to setup, edit and delete customer account is similar to that for suppliers within KSSBooks. \r Customer Account features:\r \r   Default global settings for sales account and terms; customizable for each individual customer \r   Unlimited billing addresses\r   Unlimited shipping addresses\r    Individual sales rep default assignment \r   Fr