'0','en_us','01','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch01-Introduction/welcome.html','Introduction','Introduction','Introduction     Introduction This manual is organized as follows:  Chapter 1 - Introduction Chapter 2 - General Information Chapter 3 - Installation Chapter 4 - Company Setup Chapter 5 - Accounting Tutorial and Resources Chapter 6 - Users and Security Chapter 7 - Users Manual  Chapter 8 - How To\'s Chapter 9 - Shipping Modules Chapter 10 - Importing and Exporting Chapter 11 - Reports and Forms Chapter 12 - XML Interfaces Chapter 13 - Error Messages Chapter 14 - Payment Modules  Chapter 15 - Programmer\'s Reference Chapter 16 - Test Specification Chapter 17 -  Chapter 18 -  Chapter 19 -  Chapter 20 - Glossary'),(80,81,'d','en_us','02.02','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch02-GeneralInformation/Features.html','KSSBooks.Features','KSSBooks Features','KSSBooks Features\r \r \r \r \r KSSBooks Features\r KSSBooks was created as a full featured ERP/accounting system designed to run in an internet environment. Based on the administrator interface of the well established ZenCart shopping cart application. KSSBooks features include:\r Full Featured Installation Script\r \r    Derived from the fabulous installation script used in Zencart. kssbooks will guide you through the installation including the chart of accounts, fiscal years and default cost account settings. \r \r Customer Features \r \r   Individual customer credit terms \r   Unlimited shipping and billing addresses\r   Individual sales accounts \r   Receive payments through large number of payment modules, checks, and cash \r   Sales Orders, Invoices and Point of Sale capability\r   Full featured order status window allow for easy organization and review of orders at all status levels \r \r Supplier Features \r \r   Individual supplier payment terms\r   Unilimed supplier ship from addresses and remit to addresses \r   Individually assignable expense accounts \r \r Inventory Features \r \r   Handles different types of inventory items: Stock, Assemblies, Master Stock, Non-Stock, Service, Labor, and Description Only\r    Individual inventory cost methods: FIFO, LIFO, and Average \r   Multi-tier pricing, up to 5 price levels\r   Inventory Stock level management\r   Individually assigned cost accounts for sales, inventory, and cost of sales\r    Serial number tracking capability\r    Customizable inventory group/field manager. Add as many inventory attributes as needed, in as many groupings as needed to help organize and fully define you products \r \r Banking Features \r \r   Receive payments from customers\r   Pay suppliers, write checks directly from KSSBooks\r   Payment manager allow payments of multiple suppliers at a time \r   Reconcile receipts/payments with bank statement\r   Handle Payroll with employees (future upgrade) \r \r Human Resources Features\r \r   Maintain employee information\r   Linked to the payroll feature \r \r Import/Export Features\r \r   Extensive/programmable export feature allow for individual field selection, order\r   Allows fields to be processed prior to export (e.g. format a currency, round a number, etc.)\r    Filters allow for selective exporting of just the fields desired \r   User selected field delimiters and text qualifiers to create common csv and tsv (tabbed) formats\r   Export of customer, supplier, inventory, banking, employee and general ledger data\r \r External Interfaces\r \r   Modularized interfaces available to third party applications\r   Included interface to ZenCart shopping cart system \r   Download online orders from shopping cart systems with a push of a button\r   Upload product information from KSSBooks to your shopping cart system to allow for a single database solution \r \r Multi-Company Features \r \r   Capable of handling multiple companies with individual databases.\r   New companies can be created through the setup script or copied from an existing company\r \r Report/Form Features\r \r   Includes many standard reports and forms to get up and running out of the box\r   Robust report builder tool allows creation of custom reports and forms\r   Ability to create documents in A3, A4 and Letter size paper, portrait and landscape orientation \r \r Payment Modules \r \r   Payment modules to allow for multiple payment methods\r   Easily expanded with additional payment modules \r \r Shipping/Freight Features\r \r   Modular shipping tool allows for direct interfacing to many popular freight cariers\r   Included modules: free shipping, flat rate, UPS, FedEx, and more. \r   Shipping manager tool allows for multi-piece shipments that exceed the individual package weight allowed by carriers\r    Shipping tool links directly to the order screens. Ship from and ship to addresses automatically fill the shipping manager window and drops freight selection back into order, reducing errors \r \r Security\r \r   Every menu choice has programmed security access (none, read-only, enter, edit and full) on an individual user level\r   Runs under a SSL or non-SSL environment \r   Separate user account for each company (in a multi-company environment) \r \r Other Features\r \r   Uses pop-up windows to quickly navigate and locate the information you need\r   Based on the full featured ZenCart shopping cart system administrator menu\r   Style sheet templates are compatible with the ZenCart template definitions to create a common \'look and feel\' across the two applications \r   Backup feature to protect valuable company data \r   Multi-language feature allows individual users to operate in the language of their choice \r   Platform independent\r   Web based to allow access from any browser, anywhere \r \r &nbsp;'),(81,0,'0','en_us','02','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch02-GeneralInformation/GeneralInformation.html','KSSBooks.General Information','General Information','General Information\r \r \r \r \r General Information\r This section covers the general information and overview of the KSSBooks ERP system. \r KSSBooks Features\r KSSBooks Project Goals'),(82,81,'d','en_us','02.01','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch02-GeneralInformation/ProjectGoals.html','KSSBooks.Goals','Project Goals and Objectives','Project Goals and Objectives\r \r \r \r \r Project Goals and Objectives\r The goals of KSSBooks is to develop a multi-language, accounting/ERP application freely available to everyone. KSSBooks is targeted toward the SOHO and small business community.'),(83,93,'d','en_us','03.01','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/01-PreRequisites.html','Installation.Pre-requisites','Pre-requisites','Pre-requisites\r \r \r \r \r Pre-requisites\r Prior to running the setup script. the following items need to be verified:\r System Requirements \r During the setup script, KSSBooks will inspect your system and let you know of any missing or downlevel pre-requisites. The setup script will not continue until these pre-requisites are met.\r \r   Mysql Version: 4.0 or higher \r   PHP Version: 5.0 and higher \r \r Customization Requirements \r \r   To load your own chart of accounts (versus one of the example charts), a file needs to be generated and put into the /modules/install/charts directory. Refer to the chart of accounts help file for format information.'),(84,86,'d','en_us','03.02.01','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/02-01-ChartOfAccounts.html','Installation.Chart of Accounts','Example Chart of Accounts','Example Chart of Accounts\r \r \r \r \r  Chart of Accounts\r KSSBooks contains several example chart of accounts that can be entered during setup. There is also a provision to import your own chart of accounts during the set-up process. Your custom chart of accounts file should be placed into the directory /modules/install/charts before the setup script is executed. The file requirements are as follows:\r File Type: Text (.php extension)\r   Format: php syntax as follows:\r Comments -  preceeded by a //\r   Variable $chart_description - defines the title of the chart of accounts\r   Autoincrement Array Variable $chart_array - contains three elements (1) Account Number (alphanumeric), (2) Description, (3) Account_type code.\r The Account types are:\r 0 - Cash\r   2 - Accounts Receivable\r   4 - Inventory\r   6 - Other Current Assets\r   8 - Fixed Assets\r   10 - Accumulated Depreciation\r   12 - Other Assets\r   20 - Accounts Payable\r   22 - Other Current Liabilities\r   24 - Long Term Liabilities\r   30 - Income\r   32 - Cost of Sales\r   34 - Expenses\r   40 - Equity - Doesn\\\'t Close\r   42 - Equity - Gets Closed\r   44 - Equity - Retained Earnings\r \r The example below is a snippet from the USA General Retail chart of accounts: \r &lt;?php\r   // Chart of Accounts for USA simple General company\r   $chart_description = &quot;US - General store simple Chart of Accounts&quot;;\r $chart_array = array();\r $chart_array[] = array(\'1060\',\'Checking Account\',\'0\');\r   $chart_array[] = array(\'1065\',\'Petty Cash\',\'0\');\r   $chart_array[] = array(\'1200\',\'Accounts Receivables\',\'2\');\r   $chart_array[] = array(\'1205\',\'Allowance for doubtful accounts\',\'2\');\r   \r .\r .\r .\r $chart_array[] = array(\'5800\',\'Licenses\',\'34\');\r $chart_array[] = array(\'5810\',\'Foreign Exchange Loss\',\'34\');\r ?&gt;'),(85,86,'d','en_us','03.02.02','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/02-02-SSLFactors.html','Installation.SSL Considerations','To SSL or not to SSL','To SSL or not to SSL\r \r \r \r \r To SSL or not to SSL\r KSSBooks can run in either an secure SSL environment or non-SSL environment. Although it is not necessary to determine in which mode to operate prior to running the setup script, it is prefered. Changing the operating mode is possible by editting the includes/configure.php file.'),(86,93,'0','en_us','03.02','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/02-PreInstallInfo.html','Installation.Data Pre-requisites','Pre-installation Required Information','Pre-installation Required Information     Pre-installation Required Information User the following checklist to help in verifying you have all the information necesary prior to running the setup script.         Complete     Description           &nbsp;     Download and unpack the necessary files            &nbsp;     Upload the files to your server in the desired directory           &nbsp;     Create the database table (note the database name, username, and user password)                &nbsp;     &nbsp;           &nbsp;     &nbsp;           &nbsp;     &nbsp;           &nbsp;     &nbsp;           &nbsp;     &nbsp;           &nbsp;     &nbsp;     &nbsp;'),(87,93,'d','en_us','03.03','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/03-SetupScript.html','Installation.Setup Script','Running the Setup Script','Running the Setup Script\r \r \r \r \r Running the Setup Script\r Prior to setup you will want to ensure that the directory you are installing to is accessible from a web browser. You will also want to ensure that you have access to a database and have the database name, user name and password.\r \r \r Unzip file into the desired directory on your server.\r \r In a web browser, go to the location you unzipped the files to. You should receive a message stating that the configure.php was not found and a link to install the program. When you click the link you will be taken to the welcome page.\r \r \r Welcome\r \r You can read read through the information on the welcome page and then click continue.\r \r \r License\r \r Read and accept the user license and click continue.\r \r \r Prerequisites\r \r The installer will now check for the required files and directories. If there are any unmet dependencies that prevent continuing installation these will be shown in a warning box at the top of the page. You can click the \'more info\' link next to unmet dependencies for information on how to fix the problem. \r It is common for the MySQL database to be in red since the program may not yet have access to the database. This WIL NOT prevent installation.\r \r You will also want to look at the bottom of the prerequisites page to ensure you have the correct file permissions set.\r \r Once all of the required dependencies are met you can click install at the bottom of the page.\r \r \r System Setup\r \r You will now be  asked the enter the directory or http(s) paths you want to use for various services.  You can change these if you like but the defaults should work for most installations. You will also be asked if you want to enable SSL.  Unless you know you have SSL working and want to use it you should leave this set to \'NO\'.\r \r Select \'Save Settings\' once you have finished filling out all the boxes.\r \r \r Database Setup\r \r Database Type - Select the type of database you are using from the drop down menu.\r \r Database Table - Prefix - In most cases this will be left blank.  You can enter a prefix if you are using a single database for multiple applications.\r \r Database Host - Default is localhost but you may enter another host name or IP address if database is not hosted locally.\r \r Database Username - Username you entered when setting up database.\r \r Database Password - Password you entered when setting up database.\r \r Company Database Name - Enter the name of the database you setup.  Contact the hosting provider if you are unsure.\r \r \r Admin Setup\r \r Enter your Administrator name, password and email.  You can also choose whether you would like to check for updates when logging in.\r \r \r Company Setup\r \r Enter your company\'s information and click save.\r \r \r Chart of Accounts\r \r Choose a chart of accounts most appropriate for your company.  Details of each chart can be viewed by selecting an account type and clicking \'view chart details\' link. Save settings once you have made your selection.\r \r \r Fiscal Year Setup\r \r Choose the date and year you want your fiscal year to begin and save.\r \r \r Account Defaults\r \r KSSBooks will attempt to determine the correct account numbers for the given items.  This can be changed later but now is a good time to ensure that all of the account numbers are correct for the given items.\r \r \r Finished\r \r Your setup of KSSBooks is now complete.  This page will provide some information on further steps to help you configure KSSBooks for your company\'s needs.\r \r Make sure you set permissions on your configure.php, located in the /includes folder, back to read only.\r \r Remove or rename your modules/install folder so that the system cannot be re-installed which would wipe out your existing database.'),(88,91,'d','en_us','03.04.01','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/04-01-configPHP.html','Installation.Modifying configure.php','Modifying configure.php','Modifying configure.php\r \r \r \r \r Modifying configure.php\r The file /includes/configure.php contains critical setup information necessary to run KSSBooks. It is created during the setup process and generally shouldn\'t be touched (except to make it read-only).\r the following constant variables are set in configure.php during the setup script:\r \r   HTTP_SERVER - Main webserver: eg, http://localhost - should not be empty for production servers\r   HTTPS_SERVER - Secure webserver: eg, https://localhost - should not be empty for production servers\r   ENABLE_SSL_ADMIN - secure webserver\r   DIR_WS_ADMIN - url path (these paths are relative to top of your webspace)\r   DIR_FS_ADMIN - The physical path is a COMPLETE path to your KSSBooks files.\r   DEFAULT_LANGUAGE - define the default language (can also be changed at login) \r   DB_TYPE - databse type (currently only mysql is supported) \r   DB_PREFIX - If kssbooks shares the database with other applications, a table prefix may be used.\r \r &nbsp;'),(89,91,'d','en_us','03.04.02','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/04-02-BeginningBalances.html','Installation.Beginning Balances','Entering Beginning Balances','Entering Beginning Balances\r \r \r \r \r Entering Beginning Balances\r Unless KSSBooks is set up on a new company, there will probalby be a need to transfer beginning balances from your old accounting system.   The follwing tables define the data structures required to import inventory valuation and balances as well as Payables and Receivables balances.\r Inventory\r Before beginning balances can be set up, inventory items need to be imported (or entered) into KSSBooks. Refer to manual pages on importing/exporting data for the procedure and more information.\r NOTE: If any part of the beginning balances needs to be re-entered, the only option at this time is to purge the GL and history records through the General Ledger -&gt; Utilities -&gt; Purge Journal Entries option. Note that purging the journal entries will clean out the journals and history records. It will not affect the customer or supplier accounts. \r File format \r Type: csv (comma separated variables)\r   Delimiter: comma (,)\r   Qualifier: double-quote (&quot;)\r File extension must be .csv or .txt \r Header Lines: 1  (header fields as identifed in the table below)\r Column contents\r Each entry of the inventory beginning balances should have to following information. Required fields are marked with a *. \r \r   \r     Field Name \r     Description\r   \r   \r     *sku\r     The item sku as defined on the inventory database. Must match exactly, case sensitive. \r   \r   \r     *gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to use to offset the inventory value. This account should be an \'equity-doesn\'t close\' type of account. \r   \r   \r     *inv_gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to store the inventory value. This should be and \'inventory\' type of account. \r   \r   \r     *quantity\r     The quantity of the sku to set as the beginning inventory balance.\r   \r   \r     *total_amount\r     The total value of the inventory item in the default currency. The unit cost will be calculated by dividing the total cost by the quantity.\r   \r   \r     &nbsp;\r      Serialized items - cannot be imported at this time \r     \r   \r \r Notes:\r \r    The beginning balances script will verify the sku is valid, GL accounts are valid. If any of these are found to be true, the script will terminate and no entries will be added to the databases. The script will also verify the the quantity is non-zero. If a zero quantity is found, the script will skip the entry and proceed to the next entry.\r \r Purchase Orders \r Importing purchase orders can be performed without first importing the your supplier accounts. The import routine will create the account if it cannot be found. POs with multiple line items must be consecutive to ensure that they are included in the same journal entry. \r File format \r Type: csv (comma separated variables)\r   Delimiter: comma (,)\r   Qualifier: double-quote (&quot;)\r   File extension must be .csv or .txt \r   Header Lines: 1 (header fields as identifed in the table below)\r Column contents\r Each entry of the purchase order should have to following information. Required fields are marked with a *. \r \r   \r     Field Name \r     Description\r   \r   \r     *account_id\r     The Short Name of the supplier that the purchase order should be entered against. This must match exactly to the short name of the supplier existing in the system (or it will be created).\r   \r   \r     *gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to apply the purchase order. This should be an \'accounts payable\' type of account. This account must be the same for all line items of the same PO number. \r   \r   \r     *inv_gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to use for the inventory line item. This account should be an \'inventory\' or \'expense\' type of account. \r   \r   \r     total_amount\r     The total value of the purchase order in the default currency.\r   \r   \r     freight_total\r     The total freight amount of the purchase order.\r   \r   \r     tax_total\r     The total sales tax amount of the purchase order.\r   \r   \r     *order_id\r     Purchase Order  number of this entry. Used for account tracking and payment identification.\r   \r   \r     *post_date\r     Date of the purchase order.\r   \r   \r     *bill_primary_name\r     The primary name of the accounts mailing address. Can be a company name or inidvidual name. \r   \r   \r     bill_contact\r     The contact (or attention) line for the account.\r   \r   \r     *bill_address1\r     The first mailing address line.\r   \r   \r     bill_address2\r     The second mailing address line. \r   \r   \r     *bill_city_town\r     The mailing city or town. \r   \r   \r     *bill_state_province\r     The mailing state or province. \r   \r   \r     bill_postal_code\r     The mailing postal/zip code . \r   \r   \r     *bill_country_code\r     The ISO 3 character country code. (USA, CAN, AUS, etc.) \r   \r   \r     telephone1\r     The account primary telephone number.\r   \r   \r     telephone2\r     The account altrernate telephone number.\r   \r   \r     fax\r     The account fax number.\r   \r   \r     email\r     The account e-mail address.\r   \r   \r     website\r     The acount website.\r   \r   \r     *sku\r     The line item SKU. Only one SKU per line. \r   \r   \r     *description\r     The line item description of the SKU. \r   \r   \r     *quantity\r     The quantity ordered.\r   \r   \r     *total_cost\r     The line item total price. The unit price will be calculated by (total price / quantity).\r     \r   \r \r Notes:\r \r   The billing information will be used as the bill to address for purchase orders. \r    The script will verify the account (Short Name) is valid (or a new account will be created).\r    GL accounts will be verified.\r   If the post date is not within the currently defined fiscal years (including bad format) the record will be placed in accounting period 1. \r   If any other errors are found, the script will terminate and no entries will be added to the databases. \r   If the beginning balance file is imported successfully, DO NOT REPEAT the import. The new entries will be added to the prior successful import and duplicate the payables. The import operation will not be posted unless the entire file is read in correctly and the success message is displayed.\r   The ship to address is assumed to be the company default address. \r \r Accounts Payable\r Importing payables can be performed without first importing the your supplier accounts. The import routine will create the account if it cannot be found.\r File format \r Type: csv (comma separated variables)\r   Delimiter: comma (,)\r   Qualifier: double-quote (&quot;)\r   File extension must be .csv or .txt \r   Header Lines: 1 (header fields as identifed in the table below)\r Column contents\r Each entry of the accounts payable beginning balances should have to following information. Required fields are marked with a *. \r \r   \r     Field Name \r     Description\r   \r   \r     *account_id\r     The Short Name of the supplier that the purchase order should be entered against. This must match exactly to the short name of the supplier existing in the system (or it will be created).\r   \r   \r     *gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to apply the purchase order. This account should be an \'equity-doesn\'t close\' type of account. \r   \r   \r     *inv_gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to use for the inventory line item. This account should be an \'inventory\' or \'expense\' type of account. \r   \r   \r     *total_amount\r     The total value of the payable in the default currency.\r   \r   \r     freight_total\r     The total freight amount of the purchase order.\r   \r   \r     tax_total\r     The total sales tax amount of the purchase order.\r   \r   \r     order_id\r     Invoice number of this entry. Used for account tracking and payment identification. If left blank, the waiting for invoice box will be checked.\r   \r   \r     *post_date\r     Date of the invoice. Used calculate aging of payables. \r   \r   \r     *bill_primary_name\r     The primary name of the accounts mailing address. Can be a company name or inidvidual name. \r   \r   \r     bill_contact\r     The contact (or attention) line for the account.\r   \r   \r     *bill_address1\r     The first mailing address line.\r   \r   \r     bill_address2\r     The second mailing address line. \r   \r   \r     *bill_city_town\r     The mailing city or town. \r   \r   \r     *bill_state_province\r     The mailing state or province. \r   \r   \r     bill_postal_code\r     The mailing postal/zip code . \r   \r   \r     *bill_country_code\r     The ISO 3 character country code. (USA, CAN, AUS, etc.) \r   \r   \r     telephone1\r     The account primary telephone number.\r   \r   \r     telephone2\r     The account alternate telephone number.\r   \r   \r     fax\r     The account fax number.\r   \r   \r     email\r     The account e-mail address.\r   \r   \r     website\r     The acount website.\r   \r \r Notes:\r \r   The default company information will be used as the ship to address for payables and only a single line item will be entered identified as \'Beginning Balances Entry\'. \r    The script will verify the account (Short Name) is valid (or a new account will be created).\r    GL accounts will be verified.\r   If the invoice is left blank or null, the Waiting For Payment flag will be set. \r   If the post date is not within the currently defined fiscal years (including bad format) the record will be placed in accounting period 1. \r   The script will verify the the invoice amount is non-zero. If a zero amount is found, the script will skip the entry and proceed to the next entry. In this case, the skipped records will be identified by row number. \r   If any other errors are found, the script will terminate and no entries will be added to the databases. \r   If the beginning balance file is imported successfully, DO NOT REPEAT the import. The new entries will be added to the prior successful import and duplicate the payables. The import operation will not be posted unless the entire file is read in correctly and the success message is displayed.\r   Supplier history accounts will not be updated by this procedure. \r   The ship to address is assumed to be the company default address. \r \r Sales Orders \r Importing sales orders can be performed without first importing the your custoemr accounts. The import routine will create the account if it cannot be found. SOs with multiple line items must be consecutive to ensure that they are included in the same journal entry. \r File format \r Type: csv (comma separated variables)\r   Delimiter: comma (,)\r   Qualifier: double-quote (&quot;)\r   File extension must be .csv or .txt \r   Header Lines: 1 (header fields as identifed in the table below)\r Column contents\r Each entry of the sales order should have to following information. Required fields are marked with a *. \r \r   \r     Field Name \r     Description\r   \r   \r     *account_id\r     The Short Name of the customer that the purchase order should be entered against. This must match exactly to the short name of the customer existing in the system (or it will be created).\r   \r   \r     *gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to apply the sales order. This should be an \'accounts receivable type of account. This account must be the same for all line items of the same sales order number. \r   \r   \r     *inv_gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to use for the inventory line item. This account should be an \'inventory\' or \'expense\' type of account. \r   \r   \r     total_amount\r     The total value of the sales order in the default currency.\r   \r   \r     freight_total\r     The total freight amount of the sales order.\r   \r   \r     tax_total\r     The total sales tax amount of the sales order.\r   \r   \r     *order_id\r     Sales Order number of this entry. Used for account tracking and payment identification.\r   \r   \r     *post_date\r     Date of the sales order.\r   \r   \r     *bill_primary_name\r     The primary name of the accounts mailing address. Can be a company name or inidvidual name. \r   \r   \r     bill_contact\r     The contact (or attention) line for the account.\r   \r   \r     *bill_address1\r     The first mailing address line.\r   \r   \r     bill_address2\r     The second mailing address line. \r   \r   \r     *bill_city_town\r     The mailing city or town. \r   \r   \r     *bill_state_province\r     The mailing state or province. \r   \r   \r     bill_postal_code\r     The mailing postal/zip code . \r   \r   \r     *bill_country_code\r     The ISO 3 character country code. (USA, CAN, AUS, etc.) \r   \r   \r     telephone1\r     The account primary telephone number.\r   \r   \r     telephone2\r     The account altrernate telephone number.\r   \r   \r     fax\r     The account fax number.\r   \r   \r     email\r     The account e-mail address.\r   \r   \r     website\r     The acount website.\r   \r   \r     ship_primary_name\r     The primary name of the accounts shipping address. Can be a company name or inidvidual name. \r   \r   \r     ship_contact\r     The contact (or attention) line for the account.\r   \r   \r     ship_address1\r     The first shipping address line.\r   \r   \r     ship_address2\r     The second shipping address line. \r   \r   \r     ship_city_town\r     The shipping city or town. \r   \r   \r     ship_state_province\r     The shipping state or province. \r   \r   \r     ship_postal_code\r     The shipping postal/zip code . \r   \r   \r     ship_country_code\r     The ISO 3 character country code. (USA, CAN, AUS, etc.) \r   \r   \r     *sku\r     The line item SKU. Only one SKU per line. \r   \r   \r     *description\r     The line item description of the SKU. \r   \r   \r     *quantity\r     The quantity ordered.\r   \r   \r     *total_cost\r     The line item total price. The unit price will be calculated by (total price / quantity).\r   \r \r Notes:\r \r   The billing information will be used as the bill to address for sales orders. \r    The script will verify the account (Short Name) is valid (or a new account will be created).\r    GL accounts will be verified.\r   If the post date is not within the currently defined fiscal years (including bad format) the record will be placed in accounting period 1. \r   If the sales order file is imported successfully, DO NOT REPEAT the import. The new entries will be added to the prior successful import and duplicate the sales orders. The import operation will not be posted unless the entire file is read in correctly and the success message is displayed.\r \r Accounts Receivable \r Before beginning balances can be set up, customers need to be imported (or entered) into KSSBooks. Refer to manual pages on importing/exporting data for the procedure and more information.\r File format \r Type: csv (comma separated variables)\r   Delimiter: comma (,)\r   Qualifier: double-quote (&quot;)\r   File extension must be .csv\r Header Lines: 1 (header fields as identifed in the table below)\r Column contents\r Each entry of the account receivables beginning balances should have to following information. Required fields are marked with a *. \r \r   \r     Field Name \r     Description\r   \r   \r     *account_id\r     The Short Name of the supplier that the invoice should be entered against. This must match exactly to the short name of the supplier existing in the system.\r   \r   \r     *gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to apply the receivable. This should be an \'accounts receivable\' type of account.\r   \r   \r     *inv_gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to use to offset the payable value. This account should be an \'equity-doesn\'t close\' type of account. \r   \r   \r     *total_amount\r     The total value of the receivable in the default currency.\r   \r   \r     freight_total\r     The total freight amount of the invocie.\r   \r   \r     tax_total\r     The total sales tax amount of the invoice.\r   \r   \r     order_id\r     Invoice number of this entry. Used for account tracking and payment identification. If left blank, the waiting for invoice box will be checked.\r   \r   \r     *post_date\r     Date of the invoice. Used calculate aging of payables. \r   \r   \r     *bill_primary_name\r     The primary name of the accounts mailing address. Can be a company name or inidvidual name. \r   \r   \r     bill_contact\r     The contact (or attention) line for the account.\r   \r   \r     *bill_address1\r     The first mailing address line.\r   \r   \r     bill_address2\r     The second mailing address line. \r   \r   \r     *bill_city_town\r     The mailing city or town. \r   \r   \r     *bill_state_province\r     The mailing state or province. \r   \r   \r     bill_postal_code\r     The mailing postal/zip code . \r   \r   \r     *bill_country_code\r     The ISO 3 character country code. (USA, CAN, AUS, etc.) \r   \r   \r     telephone1\r     The account primary telephone number.\r   \r   \r     telephone2\r     The account alternate telephone number.\r   \r   \r     fax\r     The account fax number.\r   \r   \r     email\r     The account e-mail address.\r   \r   \r     website\r     The acount website.\r   \r   \r     ship_primary_name\r     The primary name of the accounts shipping address. Can be a company name or inidvidual name. \r   \r   \r     ship_contact\r     The contact (or attention) line for the account.\r   \r   \r     ship_address1\r     The first shipping address line.\r   \r   \r     ship_address2\r     The second shipping address line. \r   \r   \r     ship_city_town\r     The shipping city or town. \r   \r   \r     ship_state_province\r     The shipping state or province. \r   \r   \r     ship_postal_code\r     The shipping postal/zip code . \r   \r   \r     ship_country_code\r     The ISO 3 character country code. (USA, CAN, AUS, etc.) \r   \r \r Notes:\r \r    The beginning balances script will verify the account (Short Name) is valid, GL accounts are valid, invoice number exists, and the date is invalid (including bad format). If any of these are found to not match, the script will terminate and no entries will be added to the databases. The script will also verify the the amount is non-zero. If a zero amount is found, the script will skip the entry and proceed to the next entry.\r   If the beginning balance file is imported successfully, DO NOT REPEAT the import. The new entries will be added to the prior successful import and duplicate the receivables. The import operation will not be posted unless the entire file is read in correctly and the success message is displayed.\r   Supplier history accounts will not be updated by this procedure. \r \r &nbsp;'),(90,91,'d','en_us','03.04.03','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/04-03-TransferingData.html','Installation.Transfering Data','Transfering data into KSSBooks','Transfering data into KSSBooks\r \r \r \r \r Transfering data into KSSBooks\r Data from other sources can be entered, in bulk, to KSSBooks through the beginning balances functions and the import/export operation. Refer to the particular section for details in their respective operation. Here is the general guideline to transfering data into KSSBooks.\r \r   Complete the setup script to initilize the database. (Be sure to use you current chart of accounts) \r   Set-up inventory categories and fields.\r    Import Inventory Items, Customers, Suppliers and Employees.\r   Import beginning Accounts Receivable, Accounts Payable, and Inventory balances.\r   Edit the beginning balances form to match each account with your former trial balance from the previous accounting package.\r   Set the current accounting period to the current period.\r   View the Income Statement and Balance Sheet and compare with the expected account values.'),(91,93,'0','en_us','03.04','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/04-PostInstallation.html','Installation.Post-Installation','Post-Installation Considerations','Post-Installation Considerations     Post-Installation Considerations After the setup script is complete the following steps should be taken to secure your system.    Change the permissions on includes/configure.php to read-only (0x444).'),(92,93,'d','en_us','03.05','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/05-InstallationFAQ.html','Installation.FAQs','Common Installation Problems and Frequently Asked Questions','Common Installation Problems and Frequently Asked Questions\r \r \r \r \r Common Installation Problems and FAQs\r Below are some of the common errors installing kssbooks. More current information can also be found at the KSSBooks support site, http://www.kssbooks.com/pb_phpBB/index.php.\r Table of Contents\r \r   Issue 1\r   Issue 2\r \r Resolutions\r \r   \r     Issue 1 \r   \r   \r     Resolution 1\r     \r   \r   \r     Issue 2 \r   \r   \r     Resolution 2 \r   \r \r &nbsp;'),(93,0,'0','en_us','03','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/InstallationHome.html','Installation','Installation','Installation     Installation The section deals with installation concerns from downloading the distribution to post-installation. The Setup section contains information from the intial  login screen to intializing company information, setting users, permissions, etc. Installation topics:  Pre-installation    Pre-Requisites   Chart of Accounts    SSL Considerations   Pre-installation Checklist   The Setup Script     Running the setup script   Post-Installation    Transferring data   Setting up beginning balances   Installation FAQs    Frequently Asked Questions'),(94,95,'d','en_us','04.03','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch04-Setup/CharacterSets.html','Setup.Character Sets','Character Sets Setup','Character Sets Setup     Character Sets Setup &nbsp;'),(95,0,'0','en_us','04','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch04-Setup/CompanySetup.html','Setup.Introduction','Company Setup','Company Setup     Company Setup Upon initial setup, the company information is loaded in the database. If additional companies are added, they will appear at login in a pull down menu. The user will need to select the company to use at login. Once selected, the copmpany will remain in use for the duration of the session. Additional companies can be added through the Tools-&gt;Company Manager menu.'),(96,95,'d','en_us','04.02','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch04-Setup/Currencies.html','Setup.Currencies','Currencies Setup','Currencies Setup\r \r \r \r \r Currencies Setup\r KSSBooks supports multiple currencies. The default currency is set  during setup but additional currencies can be entered through the Setup-&gt;Currencies menu.\r To enter a new currency:\r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Currencies.\r   Enter the fields request in the popup form. \r   Press the Save button to save the record. \r \r To delete a currency:\r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Currencies.\r   The current currencies are listed. To delete a currency, select the delete icon for the currency to delete.\r   Confirm the deletion of the record. NOTE: If the default currency is deleted, a new default currency should be selected.\r \r Related Links'),(97,95,'d','en_us','04.01','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch04-Setup/Languages.html','Setup.Languages','Language Setup','Language Setup\r \r \r \r \r Language Setup\r Languages are automatically detected at login. However, the default language can be set in the includes/configure.php file to pre-select the language during login. \r  The login script reviews the directories under the General module to see what language modules have been installed. Each user can select their prefered language and it will remain in effect during the duration of the session. Language modules are available throught eh kssbooks website, www.KSSBooks.com.'),(98,95,'d','en_us','04.04','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch04-Setup/LocationsBranches.html','Setup.Multiple Locations','Setting up Multiple Locations','Setting up Multiple Locations\r \r \r \r \r Setting up Multiple Locations (Warehouses) \r KSSBooks supports multiple Warehouses/stores. The company information is gathered during setup but Warehouse information is entered through the Setup-&gt;Maintain Warehouses menu.\r To enter a new Warehouse:\r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Maintain Warehouses.\r   The current Warehouses are listed. To edit a Warehouse, select the edit icon for the Warehouse to edit, or, to enter a new Warehouse press the Add button.\r    Enter a Warehouse ID. Warehouse ID\'s should not contain spaces or special characters. It is best to use an abbreviation or store number as the Warehouse ID.\r   Enter the Warehouse information requested by the form. Required information is identifed by a * next to the input box.\r   Press the Save button to save the record. \r \r To delete a Warehouse:\r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Maintain Warehouses.\r   The current Warehouses are listed. To delete a Warehouse, select the delete icon for the Warehouse to delete.\r   Confirm the deletion of the record. NOTE: If the Warehouse is used in a journal record, it cannot be deleted. Instaed, check the inactive box and the Warehouse will no be shown on the pull down menus for the order forms.\r \r Related Links\r &nbsp;'),(99,95,'d','en_us','04.05','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch04-Setup/MultiCompany.html','Setup.Multiple Companies','Setting up Multiple Companies','Setting up Multiple Companies\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r Setting Up Multiple Companies\r KSSBooks requires an unique database for each company. \r NOTE: Prior to adding or copying a new company, the database must exist in the system. kssbooks WILL NOT generate the database!\r Adding a new company \r \r   Go to Tools-&gt;Company Manager.\r   Enter the database name in the Add New Company fieldset.\r   Enter the company full name in the Add New Company fieldset.\r   If you want the demo data loaded, check the Add Demo Data box. \r   Click the Add New Company button.\r \r \r   Note: When a new comany is created, a directory under /my_files is created named the same as the database. Additional directories and  system files are created under this new directory to store uploads, logs and other information pertaining to the newly created company. \r \r Copying a company \r \r   Go to Tools-&gt;Company Manager.\r   Enter the database name in the Copy Company fieldset.\r   Enter the company full name in the Copy Company fieldset.\r   Check the boxes for the information you want to transfer over to the new company. \r   Click the Copy Company button.\r \r \r   Note: When a  company is copied, a directory under /my_files is created named the same as the database. Additional directories and system files are created under this new directory to store uploads, logs and other information pertaining to the newly created company. \r \r Deleting a company\r \r   WARNING: THIS IS A NON-RECOVERABLE EVENT! ALL DATA WILL BE LOST! BE SURE TO BACK UP YOU FILES BEFORE DELETING A COMPANY.\r \r \r   Select the company from the pulldown menu in the Delete Company fieldset.\r   Click the Delete Company button and confirm the deletion.\r   All company data will be erased. This includes all database tables as well as the directory (and subdirectories) under the /my_files/ directory named after the database.\r \r &nbsp;'),(100,103,'d','en_us','05.01','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch05-AccountingTutorial/01-Tutorial.html','Tutorial.Accounting','Accounting Tutorial','Accounting Tutorial     Accounting Tutorial &nbsp;'),(101,103,'d','en_us','05.02','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch05-AccountingTutorial/02-Resources.html','Tutorial.Accounting Resources','Accounting Resources','Accounting Resources     Accounting Resources'),(102,103,'d','en_us','05.03','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch05-AccountingTutorial/03-KSSBooksSpecific.html','Tutorial.Journal Definitions','KSSBooks Journal Definitions','KSSBooks Journal Definitions\r \r \r \r \r \r \r KSSBooks Journal Definitions\r KSSBooks uses journals to hold transaction information. Every type of transaction includes an unique journal ID to indicate the type of transaction. The table below describes the journal ID\'s and their definitions. All journal entries are stored in a two database tables, journal_main and journal_item. Table journal_main contains the general information regarding the transaction, table journal_item contains the line items associated with a transaction. For example, an invoice will contain a single journal_main record and several journal_item records. The journal_item record will have a record for the invoice total, one record for each sales tax authority, one record for shipping charges, and one record for each line item in the invoice. \r \r   \r     KSSBooks Journal Definitions\r   \r   \r   \r     Journal ID \r     Transaction Type \r     Description\r   \r   \r     2\r     General Journal\r     This journal records transaction directly to the general ledger. Costs are credited or debited directly to the selected general ledger accounts. \r   \r   \r     3\r     Purchase Quote Journal \r     Used to record quotes to suppliers for purchases.\r   \r   \r     4\r     Purchase Order Journal \r     Used to record purchase orders placed with suppliers.\r   \r   \r     6\r     Purchases Journal \r     Used to record items/action received from suppliers. May or may not impact inventory. Items need net be physical, they may be bills received from suppliers for services, etc. \r   \r   \r     7\r     Supplier Credit Memo Journal \r     Used to record credit memos for suppliers for items returned. \r   \r   \r     8\r     Payroll Journal \r     Not used at the present time. Reserved for future payroll functionality. \r   \r   \r     9\r     Sales Quote Journal \r     Used to record quotes to customers. \r   \r   \r     10\r     Sales Order Journal \r     Used to record sales orders placed by customers. \r   \r   \r     12\r     Sales/Invoice Journal \r     Used to record sales of items, services, etc. to customers.\r   \r   \r     13\r     Customer Credit Memo Journal \r     Used to record returns by customers.\r   \r   \r     14\r     Inventory Assembly Journal \r     Used to record inventory items assembled. The inventory item must be of type Item Assembly. \r   \r   \r     16\r     Inventory Adjustment Journal \r     Used to record inventory adjustments. Adjustments may be positive (extra inventory) or negative (inventory loss due to pilferage, damage, etc.)\r   \r   \r     18\r     Cash Receipts Journal \r     This journal is used for all customer receipt type transactions. It is also used for Supplier Credit Memos.\r   \r   \r     19\r     Point of Sale Journal \r     Not used at the present time. For direct sales, enter the items through the sales/invoice journal and select the payment button to post the transaction and proceed to the payment receipt operation. \r   \r   \r     20\r     Cash Distribution Journal \r     This journal is used for all supplier payment type transactions. It is also used for Customer Payment entries.\r   \r   \r     21\r     Point of Purchase Journal \r     Not used at the present time. For direct purchases, enter the items through the purchase/receive journal and select the payment button to post the transaction and proceed to the payment operation. \r   \r   \r     22\r     Shipping Journal \r     Not used at the present time. This function is handled through the Shipping Manager. \r   \r \r &nbsp;'),(103,0,'0','en_us','05','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch05-AccountingTutorial/AccoutingTutorial.html','Tutorial.Basic Accounting','Accounting Tutorial and Resources','Accounting Tutorial and Resources     Accounting Tutorial and Resources'),(104,106,'d','en_us','06.01','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch06-UsersSecurity/01-CtlPanelSecurity.html','Security.Control Panel','Control Panel Security','Control Panel Security\r \r \r \r \r Control Panel Security\r The kssbooks control panel has built in security to control user access to individual control panel modules. Permissions are based on the modules most closely related to the KSSBooks module it pertains to. For example, the sales order control panel module is tied to the permission of the Customer-&gt;Sales Orders module. If the user has no access to the Sales Order function, the control panel module will be blocked as well. \r &nbsp;'),(105,106,'d','en_us','06.02','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch06-UsersSecurity/02-RptFrmSecurity.html','Security.Reports','Reports/Forms Security','Reports/Forms Security\r \r \r \r \r Reports/Forms Security\r  Kssbooks reports and forms have three levels of security: user, employee, and department. They my be used individually or in any combination. \r User security - One or more (or all by default) users may be given access to the report. \r Employee - One of more (or all by default) employees may be given access to the report.\r Department - one or more (or all by default) departments may be given access to the report.\r &nbsp;'),(106,0,'0','en_us','06','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch06-UsersSecurity/UsersMain.html','Users','Users and Security','Users and Security\r \r \r \r \r Users and Security\r Kssbooks support multiple users each assigned multi-level  security. During setup, the administrator user is defined and given full privileges. the administrator can then add additional users and set security appropriately. Each module has an unique securty id and can be set to the following levels:\r \r   None - No access. Users with this security will not see the module as part of the menu.\r   Read Only - The user can only open and read the information. they are not permitted to save and changes they make to the record. In this case, the Save icon will not be displayed.\r   Add - The user can create records but cannot edit them or delete them.\r   Edit - The user can add and edit a record but cannot delete the record. \r   Full - The user has full read/write access to the record.\r \r The add/edit a user:\r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Users.\r   The current users are listed. To edit a user, select the Edit icon for the user to edit, or, to enter a new user press the Add button.\r    Enter/edit the fields as necessary. Enter the security levels for each module as necessary. \r     NOTE: If editting a user and  the passwords fields are left blank, the password will not be affected.\r     NOTE: \r   Users may be linked to the employee list only if the employee us set up prior to the user account. \r   Press the Save icon to save the record. NOTE: the user settings will not take effect until the user logs off and back onto the system.\r \r To delete a user:\r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Users.\r   The current users are listed. To delete a user, select the Delete icon for the user to delete.\r   Confirm you choice and the user will be removed from the database.\r \r &nbsp;'),(107,110,'d','en_us','08.10','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch08-HowTo/HowTo-BegBalances.html','Beginning Balances - Setup','How To ... Beginning Balances','How To ... Beginning Balances     How To ... Setup Beginning Balances  &nbsp;'),(108,0,'d','en_us','08.03.01','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch08-HowTo/HowTo-SalesProcess.html','How To - Process a Sale','How To ... Process a Sale','How To ... Process a Sale\r \r \r \r \r How To ... Process a Sale \r Processing sales are a key part of the kssbooks capabilities. Prior to processing a sale there are many settings that are required. \r Pre-requisites:\r Inventory - Need something to sell\r   Customer - Someone to sell to (Note - Customers can be added on either the Sales Order or Sales/Invoice screen by checking the add/update button)\r   Sales Tax Authorities and Rates \r   Payment Methods - Cash and bank Check are loaded by default\r   Shipping Carriers - If shipping is necessary. FreeShipper is installed by default and can be used when no shipping is needed.\r Entering a Sale - The Process \r OPTIONAL - Customers -&gt; Customer Quote. The customer quote is optional and if entered, can be converted to a sales order or invoice. (conversion available in Release R1.4 and up) \r OPTIONAL - Customers -&gt; Sales Order. Enter the customer information or select from the popup menu. Required fields are indicated with a red star. Select the items to sell, price. Enter the tax (automatically calculated from pull down) and shipping carrier/method.\r Customers -&gt; Sales/Invoice. If a Sales Order was created, enter the customer name in the search box and press the open icon. The customer should be in the popup menu with a pull down showing all open sales orders. Select the sales order from the pull down or select Enter New to create a new sales/Invoice. All the information will be entered in the Sales/Invoice screen. If a Sales/Invoice will be generated new in this screen enter the information for both the billing and shipping required fields and enter the item(s) being purchased. Enter the tax and shipping carrier/methods. Leave the invoice number blank and KSSBooks will assign the next invoice number from the sequence. \r NOTE: The invoice may be printed here but will show a balance due. If a payment is to be received (Point of Sale), it is better to receive the payment and print out the receipt after the payment has been processed show the invoice shows the payment applied. \r Option 1: No payment received at this time (customer billed).\r Click on the pdf icon to print the invoice and/or packing slip. Only one form may be printed at a time. If an invoice and a packing slip are both needed, print one, open the invoice again and print the other. \r Option 2: Payment received\r Click on the payment icon (looks like a calculator) and the invoice will be posted and the Customer Receipts screen will appear. Enter the payment information and click the pdf icon to print the invoice with the payment showing.\r NOTE: To aid in reconciliation with the bank, code the Deposit Ticket ID in a way such that similar type are grouped together. For example, if you accept Visa, code all receipts using Visa as payment with a VISAyyyymmdd and they will be grouped together in the bank reconciliation operation to match with the credit card batch. Code checks DPyyyymmdd and all checks received (or part of a bank deposit) will be totaled and displayed as a single line item in the reconciliation screen. All checks that are part of a single bank deposit should have the same Deposit Ticket ID code. This technique aligns the  Deposit Slip report and the bank statements. Same with credit card batches (daily credit card receipts) and cash (to count the cash drawer at the end of the day).\r To ship the item, press Customers-&gt; Invoice Manager. Locate the invoice and press the Ship button. A popup will appear for the carrier selected. For most of the basic shipping carriers, a form to enter the tracking number, if any, and date will be displayed. This information is entered into the shipping log. For package carriers such as UPS or FedEx, the shipping screen will appear to enter the package information. Once entered, shipping labels will be generated and can be printed (on either plain paper through pdf format or thermal label printer). For these carriers, the shipping log will be filled in automatically after the labels have been generated and the tracking information is known.\r NOTE: To re-print the labels or track the package, press Tools -&gt; Shipping and select the tab of the carrier. \r &nbsp;'),(109,0,'d','en_us','08.04.01','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch08-HowTo/HowTo-ZenCart.html','ZenCart Interface','How To ... ZenCart Interface','How To ... ZenCart Interface\r \r \r \r \r How To ... Setup the ZenCart Interface\r KSSBooks has a built in interface with the ZenCart e-commerce shopping cart. The interface provide the following functionality:\r \r   Download orders from Zencart to KSSBooks\r   Upload products to ZenCart from KSSBooks \r \r Pre-requisites\r  Order Download Function - None \r Inventory Upload Function - Additional inventory fields are required to match up with the fields used in ZenCart. It is recommended that a new inventory category be added containing the fields needed for the ZenCart interface.\r \r   \r     Field Name\r     (case sensitive) \r     Field Type \r     Description\r   \r   \r     catalog\r     Checkbox\r     Used to identify products that can be uploaded to ZenCart. If the checkbox is selected, an icon will appear allowing the pdoduct to be uploaded to ZenCart. \r   \r   \r     category_id\r     TextField\r     Needs to match exactly with the category as defined in ZenCart. The ZenCart category must be the lowest level in the category tree. \r   \r   \r     manufacturer\r     TextField\r     Needs to match exactly with the manufacturer as defined in ZenCart.\r   \r \r Installing the files in ZenCart \r At the ZenCart enable website, the Wincominfotech KSSBooks-ZenCart module needs to be installed. the package is available at the KSSBooks website and the ZenCart website.\r \r   Unzip the files into the Zencart folder and follow the installation instructions. \r   Install the functions desired.\r   Configure the functions per the module installation instructions. When pointing the ZenCart download functions, use url: https://yourdomain.com/KSSBooksDir/modules/soap/(function).php. i.e. order.php for downloaded orders. (HTTP:// may be used for non-SSL transactions) \r \r Installing the ZenCart Module \r \r   From the Tools -&gt; ZenCart Interface menu select the function to activate and press Install.\r   Press edit to set the parameters for the interface function (see each function detail below for parameters to set).\r   After the parameters have been set, press Update to save the changes.\r \r Setting the function parameters\r Order Download Function \r \r   After installing the function. The only parameters to set are the enable/disable checkbox and the sort order. \r \r Inventory Upload Function \r \r   Install the function if not already installed. \r   Press the Edit button to enter edit mode.\r   Click the enable checkbox.\r   Set the sort order to a non-zero value.\r    For the KSSBooks XML URL, enter https://yourdomain.com/ZencartDir/admin/soap/products.php.\r   Enter an admin username and password. This can be an existing user, or better, a new user whose activity can be monitored in the admin log file.\r   If price sheets are to be used to set the upload pricing, set the True radsio button and then select a price sheet from the pull down menu. NOTE: At least one price sheet needs to be defined to upload using price sheets. If price sheets are not used, the Retail or Full Price will be used.\r \r Using the ZenCart Functions \r Order Download Function\r \r   Orders can b downloaded by logging into your Zencart shoppping cart and selecting Customers -&gt; Orders. From the order screen an icon will be added indicating whether an order has been downloaded or not. If not, press the icon and the order will be downloaded to KSSBooks (as a sales order) and the order page will reload. The download icon for the order downloaded will not be shown indicating the order was successfully downloaded to KSSBooks. \r   If there are download errors during the process, an error message will be displayed. Fix the error and retry. \r \r Inventory Upload Function\r \r   Select Inventory -&gt; Maintain. The list of inventory items will be displayed with an upload icon appearing next to the products that have been identified as catalog items. (Catalog items are items that have the added inventory field catalog checked)\r   If there are upload errors during the process, an error message will be displayed. Fix the error and retry. \r \r Additional Information\r Adding Inventory Categories\r Adding Inventory Fields Adding Price Sheets\r &nbsp;'),(110,0,'0','en_us','08','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch08-HowTo/HowToHome.html','How To ...','How To ...','How To ...     How To ... Installation &nbsp; Company Setup &nbsp; Receivables &nbsp; Payables &nbsp; Inventory &nbsp; Banking &nbsp; General Ledger &nbsp; Employees &nbsp; Importing/Exporting &nbsp; Reports and Forms  &nbsp;'),(111,123,'0','en_us','09.01','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/01-Modules/ModulesHome.html','Shipping Modules','Shipping Modules','Shipping Modules\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules\r \r KSSBooks has a built in Shipping Manager module to aid in the generation of rates and labels for your products. Additional modules may be added to further enhance the number of shipping options. A shipping log is kept with pertinent inforamton to monitor your packages and verify status. \r Standard Shipping Modules\r Federal Express (FedEx) - Includes rates, label generation, tracking, and logging \r United Parcel Service (UPS) - Includes rates, label generation, tracking, and logging \r United States Postal Service (USPS) - rates, logging \r Flat Rate Shipping - rates, logging \r Free Shipping - rates, logging \r Per Item Shipping - rates, logging \r Store Pickup (Will Call) - rates, logging \r Table Rate Based Shipping  - rates, logging \r Zone (State/Province) Based Shipping  - rates, logging \r Related Links\r How to Set up Shipping Defaults\r Invoice Manger\r Adding new Shipping Modules\r Removing Shipping Modules'),(112,111,'d','en_us','09.01.01','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/01-Modules/fedex/FedExHome.html','Shipping Modules.FedEx','Shipping Modules - FedEx','Shipping Modules - FedEx\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules - FedEx\r KSSBooks includes a shipping module to integrate with Federal Express through their APIs. Companies must have a FedEx shipper number and register with FedEx.com to request a meter number before the module will function correctly. \r Features Include:\r \r   Request for meter number.\r   Freight quotes for Ground, Home Delivery, Express, Express Freight, and Freight (Ground LTL)\r   Label generation for Express, Ground, Home Delivery, and Express Freight\r   Shipping Manager integration\r    Customer and Supplier order integration.\r   Integration with Invoice Manger \r   Tracking integration\r   Multi-piece shipments \r   Report capability available through reportwriter. \r \r How to Install FedEx Shipping/Request a Meter Number \r \r   Through Setup -&gt; Shipping Settings, click on the FedEx Service row in the table and a button labeled Install will appear on the right. \r   Click on Install to install the FedEx module. \r   Click the FedEx row again and Click on the Edit Button.\r   Select True to enable the module, enter your FedEx account number and FedEx Freight number if you want to use the service. Leave the meter number field blank. Select Test Mode and your desired Printer Type. Select the services you want to offer and press Update.\r   Request a Meter Number: Click the FedEx Edit button again and press the Request a Meter Number button (which will appear if your fedex number is present but the meter number is blank). An XML request will be sent to FedEx with your company\'s information (as defined in Company -&gt; My Company) and account number to register with FedEx API servers. A popup window will appear if the transaction was successful with your meter number. WRITE IT DOWN! If you accidentally un-install the module, the meter number is not saved and you will have to repeat the request. Enter the meter number in the Meter Number field and press Update. \r   FedEx requires sample labels to be mailed to them to validate the quality of the image. Refer to FedEx.com for further information.\r   After approval from FedEx with your sample labels, Edit the FedEx shipping settings and change the Test Mode to Production. You will need to request a new meter number for the production servers before an actual label can be generated. \r \r Note: Place the sort order to a number greater than zero. IF THE SORT ORDER IS ZERO, IT WILL NOT SHOW UP. \r How the Get a Rate Quote\r \r   Rate quotes are available from the order screens. When shipping is enabled (Company -&gt; My Company -&gt; Enable Shipping Settings) a button will appear next to the freight method and price to load the shipping popup and request a rate. \r   The Shipping Quote popup will be mostly filled out with values pulled from the order and the shipping defaults. Changes , however can be made before the carrier servers are queried for rates.\r   Once the information in the shipping popup has been verified, Press the Next button and the rate estimator will pull the quoted rates form the selected services.\r   Click on the rate desired and the carrier, method, and rate information will be entered into the order form; the popup will close. \r \r Note: If the weight field of inventory items is filled out, the weight of the shipment will be automatically calculated and inserted into the rate estimator. \r How to Print a Label\r Labels can be printed manually through Shipping Manager or, for a particular invoice, through the Invoice Manager. If Invoice Manager is used, most of the information will be pre-entered into the label form. Verification of information and the package details are all that is needed. If a label is generated from Shipping Manager. the destination address must be entered and the package information.\r From Invoice Manager\r \r   Select Customers -&gt; Invoice Manager. Invoices are listed  in descending order by invoice number.\r   Locate the invoice to generate a label from and press the Ship button. NOTE: Once a package has been shipped, the button will change to Void Shipment and the invoice cannot be re-shipped. \r   A popup form will appear with most of the fields filled in. The field information is derived from the invoice itself along with default values set in the Company -&gt; Shipping Defaults settings.\r   Enter the package weight, dimensions and insurance value. If more than one package is to be shipped with this invoice (Multi-piece), press the Plus sign to add another package row. \r   After all information has been entered, press the PDF icon and the label will be retrieved from FedEx. \r   Once the label has been retrieved, the window will contain either a button to download the image (thermal printers) or a PDF image will appear in the window.\r   Print the label to the appropriate printer. NOTE: For thermal labels, the label must be printed in RAW format directly to the printer port. In this case, the label must be downloaded and saved locally, The file must then be copied (or moved) directly to the port the thermal printer is connected to. \r   Once all labels have been printed, close the label manager popup widow. \r \r From Shipping Manager\r \r   Select Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager.\r   Click on the Ship a Package button.\r   A popup form will appear with shipping default fields filled in. The field information is derived from the default values set in the Company -&gt; Shipping Defaults settings.\r   Enter the address information to ship the package. \r   Enter the package weight, dimensions and insurance value. If more than one package is to be shipped with this invoice (Multi-piece), press the Plus sign to add another package row. \r   After all information has been entered, press the PDF icon and the label will be retrieved from FedEx. \r   Once the label has been retrieved, the window will contain either a button to download the image (thermal printers) or a PDF image will appear in the window.\r   Print the label to the appropriate printer. NOTE: For thermal labels, the label must be printed in RAW format directly to the printer port. In this case, the label must be downloaded and saved locally, The file must then be copied (or moved) directly to the port the thermal printer is connected to. \r   Once all labels have been printed, close the label manager popup widow.\r \r How to Re-Print a Label\r \r       From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, locate the package to re-print the label. Click on the printer icon on the package line. NOTE: All labels are stored in the my_files directory on the server. re-printing will not re-query FedEx but merely reload the image file from the original request. \r   Once the label has been retrieved (from your local my_files directory), the window will contain either a button to download the image (thermal printers) or a PDF image will appear in the window.\r   Print the label to the appropriate printer. NOTE: For thermal labels, the label must be printed in RAW format directly to the printer port. In this case, the label must be downloaded and saved locally, The file must then be copied (or moved) directly to the port the thermal printer is connected to. \r   Once all labels have been printed, close the label manager popup widow.\r \r How to Void a Shipment\r NOTE: Shipments can only be voided the same day the label was generated. \r \r   Packages can be deleted through either Invoice Manager or Ship Manager. \r   From Invoice Manger, locate the invoice to void the shipment. Press the Void Shipment button and a label void request will be sent to FedEx. NOTE: Once a shipment is voided, the button from that invoice in Invoice Manager will revert back to the Ship state where the shipment can be re-shipped if necessary.\r   From Shipping Manager, press the delete icon next to the package you want to void. Confirm the void operation and the shipment will be deleted. NOTE: FedEx will only let an entire shipment be deleted, if the shipment contains more than one package, all packages in the shipment will be voided. \r \r How to Track a Package\r \r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, select the date the package was shipped. Locate the package to track and click on the tracking number. \r   A new window will appear linked to the FedEx.com web site and the tracking information will be automatically entered. \r   Packages can also be tracked through the Invoice Manager. Locate the invoice to track, select the View Ship Log icon and a popup will appear with the shipment information. The tracking number will appear in the log, Click on the tracking icon next to it to track the package. \r \r Related Subjects\r How to Set up Shipping Defaults\r   Shipping Manager\r   Invoice Manger'),(113,111,'d','en_us','09.01.02','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/01-Modules/flat/FlatHome.html','Shipping Modules.Flat Rate','Shipping Modules - Flat Rate','Shipping Modules - Flat Rate\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules - Flat Rate\r \r KSSBooks includes a shipping module to calculate flat rate shipping charges. \r Features Include:\r \r   Freight quotes\r   Shipping Manager integration\r    Customer and Supplier order integration.\r   Integration with Invoice Manger \r   Tracking information and shipping logs \r   Report capability available through reportwriter. \r \r How to Install Flat Rate Shipping Module \r \r   Through Setup -&gt; Shipping Settings, click on the Flat Rate row in the table and a button labeled Install will appear on the right. \r   Click on Install to install the Flat Rate module. \r   Click the Flat Rate row again and Click on the Edit Button.\r   Enter the rate information and press Save to save the changes. \r \r Note: Place the sort order to a number greater than zero. IF THE SORT ORDER IS ZERO, IT WILL NOT SHOW UP. \r How the Get a Rate Quote\r \r   Rate quotes are available from the order screens. When shipping is enabled (Company -&gt; My Company -&gt; Enable Shipping Settings) a button will appear next to the freight method and price to load the shipping popup and request a rate. \r   The Shipping Quote popup will be mostly filled out with values pulled from the order and the shipping defaults. Changes , however can be made before the carrier servers are queried for rates.\r   Once the information in the shipping popup has been verified, Press the Next button and the rate estimator will pull the quoted rates form the selected services.\r   Click on the rate desired and the carrier, method, and rate information will be entered into the order form; the popup will close. \r \r Note: If the weight field of inventory items is filled out, the weight of the shipment will be automatically calculated and inserted into the rate estimator. \r How to Enter a Shipping Log Record\r \r    Shipping log entries are entered either through the Invoice Manager.\r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice to create the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Ship button on the line the invoice appears.\r   A popup will appear with a form to enter the package information.\r   Select the Service Type, shipment/Expected receipt dates, tracking information and the shipment cost.\r   Press the Save icon to save the shipment information. NOTE: Once a shipment log entry has been generated, the button on Invoice Manager changes from Ship to Void Shipment.\r \r How to Void a Shipping Log Record\r \r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice you want to void the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Void Shipment button and the shipping log entry will be deleted. NOTE: The Invoice Manager will now allow the package to be re-shipped if necessary.\r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, locate the shipment to void.\r   Press the Delete icon on the line of the shipment, confirm the void and the shipment record will be deleted.  \r \r How to Track a Package\r \r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, select the date the package was shipped. Locate the package to track. \r   Since Flat Rate shipping is not tied to a particular supplier, only the tracking number will be displayed, it can now be copied to the clipboard and pasted into the carrier site to track the package. \r \r Related Subjects\r How to Set up Shipping Defaults\r     Shipping Manager\r     Invoice Manger'),(114,111,'d','en_us','09.01.03','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/01-Modules/freeshipper/FreeHome.html','Shipping Modules.Free Shipping','Shipping Modules - Free Shipping','Shipping Modules - Free Shipping\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules - Free Shipping\r \r KSSBooks includes a shipping module to calculate free shipping charges (with handling). \r Features Include:\r \r   Freight quotes\r   Shipping Manager integration\r    Customer and Supplier order integration.\r   Integration with Invoice Manger \r   Tracking information and shipping logs \r   Report capability available through reportwriter. \r \r How to Install Freeshipper Shipping Module \r \r       Through Setup -&gt; Shipping Settings, click on the Freeshipper row in the table and a button labeled Install will appear on the right. \r       Click on Install to install the Freeshipper module. \r   Click the Freeshipper row again and Click on the Edit Button.\r   Enter the rate information and press Save to save the changes. \r \r Note: Place the sort order to a number greater than zero. IF THE SORT ORDER IS ZERO, IT WILL NOT SHOW UP. \r How the Get a Rate Quote\r \r   Rate quotes are available from the order screens. When shipping is enabled (Company -&gt; My Company -&gt; Enable Shipping Settings) a button will appear next to the freight method and price to load the shipping popup and request a rate. \r   The Shipping Quote popup will be mostly filled out with values pulled from the order and the shipping defaults. Changes , however can be made before the carrier servers are queried for rates.\r   Once the information in the shipping popup has been verified, Press the Next button and the rate estimator will pull the quoted rates form the selected services.\r   Click on the rate desired and the carrier, method, and rate information will be entered into the order form; the popup will close. \r \r Note: If the weight field of inventory items is filled out, the weight of the shipment will be automatically calculated and inserted into the rate estimator. \r How to Enter a Shipping Log Record\r \r    Shipping log entries are entered either through the Invoice Manager.\r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice to create the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Ship button on the line the invoice appears.\r   A popup will appear with a form to enter the package information.\r   Select the Service Type, shipment/Expected receipt dates, tracking information and the shipment cost.\r   Press the Save icon to save the shipment information. NOTE: Once a shipment log entry has been generated, the button on Invoice Manager changes from Ship to Void Shipment.\r \r How to Void a Shipping Log Record\r \r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice you want to void the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Void Shipment button and the shipping log entry will be deleted. NOTE: The Invoice Manager will now allow the package to be re-shipped if necessary.\r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, locate the shipment to void.\r   Press the Delete icon on the line of the shipment, confirm the void and the shipment record will be deleted. \r \r How to Track a Package\r \r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, select the date the package was shipped. Locate the package to track. \r   Since Freeshipper shipping is not tied to a particular supplier, only the tracking number will be displayed, it can now be copied to the clipboard and pasted into the carrier site to track the package. \r \r Related Subjects\r How to Set up Shipping Defaults\r     Shipping Manager\r     Invoice Manger'),(115,111,'d','en_us','09.01.04','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/01-Modules/item/ItemHome.html','Shipping Modules.Per Item','Shipping Modules - Per Item','Shipping Modules - Per Item\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules - Per Item\r \r KSSBooks includes a shipping module to calculate per item shipping charges. \r Features Include:\r \r   Freight quotes\r   Shipping Manager integration\