ation','Shipping Modules - Installation\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules - Installation\r \r Additional shipping modules can be downloaded from www.KSSBooks.com and installed into the /modules/shipping/directory. Please refer to the installation instructions included with each module for details installing the particular module.'),(122,123,'d','en_us','09.02','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/03-Removal/RemovalHome.html','Shipping Modules - Removal','Shipping Modules - Removal','Shipping Modules - Removal\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules - Removal\r \r There is no need to remove a particular shipping module. Simply uninstalling it will remove the module from appearing in any of KSSBooks functions.'),(123,0,'0','en_us','09','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/ShippingHome.html','Shipping','Shipping','Shipping\r \r \r \r \r Shipping\r \r KSSBooks contains powerful, flexible shipping tools to help estimate, ship, track and monitor your shipping needs. Several shipping modules are included with the standard distribution including FedEx, UPS and USPS along with non-carrier based shipping methods. \r Shipping Manager - The Shipping Manager tool is the main interface to the shipping functions. From here you can ship packages, track packages, review package volume and shipment costs and void shipments. \r Invoice Manager - The Invoice Manager includes a link to the shipping functions to allow for order fulfillment directly from the invoice. The invoice manager does most of the work for you by filling in the shipping form automatically. All you need to do i enter the package information and carrier approved label will be generated within KSSBooks.\r Related Links\r Shipping Modules\r   Invoice Manager\r  \r &nbsp;'),(124,0,'d','en_us','10','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch10-ImportingExporting/ImpExpHome.html','Importing','Importing/Exporting','Importing/Exporting\r \r \r \r \r Importing/Exporting\r KSSBooks has several ways to import data into the system. \r With the exception of beginning balances, import operation are made through the Tools -&gt; Import/Export menu. Beginning balances are imported through the General Ledger -&gt; General Journal Utilities menu. \r General Import Procedure \r \r   From the Tools -&gt; Import/Export menu, select the tab of the type of import you want to perform.\r   Scroll down the list and select the template to import from, press the Open icon.\r    The criteria tab will display the criteria for which to import data. This will allow filtering the imported data to only include the fields you are interested in.\r   Click on the fields tab. The table displayed lists the fields available to import. Column fields are defined as follows:\r     \r       Sequence - Indicates the sequence the field appears in the import file format.\r       Field Name - This is a textual name for identifying the field to import. It is linked to the actual database field name. \r       Processing - Kssbooks allows for processing the data during the import operation. Imported values can be trimmed, formatted, etc. to meet the criteria of the database value ranges. \r       Import - Specifies whether the field is available for import. Generally, all fields are importable except the primary index field (usually named id) \r       Show - Indicates whether the field will be included in the import list or not. Yes = include, No = don\'t include \r     \r   \r   Arrange the fields to match the sequence of the import data.\r   Save the import template for future use (it\'s best to try a few trial runs to validate the import template before importing the entire data file.\r   Press the Options tab and select the delimiter and text qualifier for the import file. Check whether the first row contains header information. The header information is ignored during the import if checked, the import is sequence driven. \r    Press the Browse button and select the file to import.\r   Press the Import icon to initiate the import. NOTE: It\'s best to try a smaller file at first on a test system until the import template is validated.\r \r General Export Procedure\r Data can be exported using the same template as importing. The data file is downloaded to your browser and can be saved or viewed locally. Another option is to use the reportwriter tool to build the export data and select the csv option when creating the report. \r Importing Contacts (Suppliers/Customers/Employees) \r Contacts can be imported into KSSBooks through csv or tab delimited format. Up to 5 of each billing and shipping addresses may be imported with each contact.\r Importing Inventory\r Inventory can be entered into KSSBooks as a csv or tab separated file. NOTE: make sure all additional inventory fields are set-up in the system before importing inventory. (See Inventory - Tabs and Fields) \r Importing Beginning Balances\r Importing beginning balances is covered in the following section: Installation - Importing Beginning Balances \r The following journals can be imported. Inventory, Purchase Orders, Purchase/receive Inventory, Sales Orders, Sales/Invoices. For inventory, the SKU\'s must be present in the system prior to importing values. For the rest, the suppliers/customers will be created during the import process, if necessary. \r Importing Chart of Accounts\r &nbsp;\r Copying Companies \r Companies can be copied to a new database along with selected information ranging from tables only to every record stored in the source company. Company operations are found in the Tools -&gt; Company Manager menu.'),(125,126,'d','en_us','12.03.01','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch12-SoapXML/03-Customers/03-01-salesorders_import.html','Sales Orders.XML Tag Definitions','Sales Order XML Definitions','Sales Order XML Definitions\r \r \r \r KSSBooks Manual\r \r   \r     Previous Chapter \r     Chapter 1 - Sales Order Interface \r     Next Chapter \r   \r \r Chapter Heading\r Table of Contents\r 1.0 Introduction\r 2.0  Change History\r 3.0 Overview\r 4.0 General Programming Information\r 4.1 Access Request Interface Specification\r 4.2 Response Request Interface Specification\r 4.3 Examples\r 5.0 Programming Information\r 5.1 Access Request Interface Specification\r 5.2 Response Request Interface Specification\r 5.3 Examples\r 6.0 Appendices\r 6.1 Glossary\r 6.2 Return Status and Error Codes\r 6.3 Reference Tables\r 6.4 Frequently Asked Questions\r 1.0 Introduction\r This chapter covers the sales order interface. \r 2.0 Change History\r \r   \r     Revision\r     Description of Change \r     Date\r   \r   \r     1.0\r     Initial Release\r     1/1/2007\r   \r   \r     &nbsp;\r     &nbsp;\r     &nbsp;\r   \r \r 3.0 Overview\r Sales orders are submitted to kssbooks through XML\r With the sales order interface you can:\r \r   Submit new sales orders  to the KSSBooks system\r   Check status of existing sales orders\r   Change open sales orders\r   Close open sales orders\r \r 4.0 General Programming Information\r Access to the interface requires an open XML account in KSSBooks, refer to user maintenance for information on creating and maintaining the XML users interface. \r Security \r DTD\'s \r SSL \r 4.1 Access Request Interface Specification\r *Yes - required if the container tag is present.\r \r   \r     Element (XMLPath) \r     Required/Cardinality\r     Type\r     Length\r     Description/Values\r   \r   \r     AccessRequest\r     Yes / One \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Access Request container tag \r   \r   \r     AccessRequest/\r     AccessUserID\r     Yes / One\r     Alpha-numeric\r     5 to 15\r     XML User ID  for request\r   \r   \r     AccessRequest/\r       AccessPassword\r     \r     Yes / One \r     Any\r     5 to 20\r     XML User Password for request \r   \r   \r     AccessRequest/\r     AccessFunction\r     Yes / One \r     Text\r     5 to 20\r     Must be \'SalesOrderEntry\' for this entry. This value matched with the username and password to verify access privileges to this function.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry\r     Yes / One \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Top level container tag for the request \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r       Request\r     Yes / One \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Container tag for the general parameters of the request\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     Request/\r     Version\r     \r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     4\r     The  XML interface version to the SalesOrder function. Current versions supported are:\r       1.00 - Intial release\r     \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     Request/\r     RequestAction\r     Yes / One \r     Text\r     15\r     The action requested for this transaction.\r          Possible options are:\r       New - New Sales Order\r       Status - Status an existing sales order\r       Change - Change an existing sales order\r       Close - Close an existing sales order\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r Request/ \r ReferenceName\r \r     No / Zero or One \r     Any\r     0 to 64\r     This field may be used to correlate the requests with the response for multiple submissions. The data from this field are returned with the response without modification. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r Request/ \r Originator\r     Yes / One \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Container tag for originator of sales order \r     \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r Request/Originator/\r StoreID\r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 16 \r     Contains the Store ID for the sales order submission. The value must correspond to a valid store ID as defined in the XML input/output configuration in KSSBooks. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r Request/Originator/\r SalesRepID\r     No / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 15 \r     Contains the Sales Rep ID for the sales order submission. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder\r     Yes / One \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Container for a single sales order. \r         NOTE: At this time only one sales order can be processed per  XML transaction. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary\r     Yes / One \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Container for the order summary information.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/\r SalesOrderID\r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 16 \r     Sales Order ID reference. This value will be the key for processing and all future references to this sales order. This number must be unique to all values from all stores within the sales order journal. If left blank or omitted, a sales order number will be generated by the receiver. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/\r SalesOrderDate\r     No / Zero or One \r     Date Format \r     10 or 19\r     Date format must be of the form \'YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS\' or abbreviated \'YYYY-MM-DD\'\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/\r ItemTotal\r     No / Zero or One \r     Numeric\r     Float\r     Subtotal for all items contained within the sales order. This value will be verified against the quantities and prices of the sales orders line items. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/\r TaxTotal\r     No / Zero or One \r     Numeric\r     Float\r     Total tax charged for this sales order. This value will be verified against the total taxes charged within the sales orders line items. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/\r ShippingTotal \r     No / Zero or One \r     Numeric\r     Float\r     Total shipping charged for this sales order.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/\r ShippingCarrier\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     3 to 15 \r     Carrier to be used for this order. Must match an existing carrier as defined in KSSBooks. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/\r ShippingMethod\r     Yes / One\r     Alpha-numeric\r     3 to 15 \r     Shipping delivery service requested for this order. Must match codes as defined in KSSBooks. Current codes are:\r     01 - Next Day Air\r       02 - Second Day Air\r       03 - Three Day Delivery\r       GD - Ground or Standard\r     \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/ \r OrderNotes\r \r     No / One \r     Text\r     0 to 255 \r     Customer or Requestor special notes associated with this order. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/ \r OrderSummary/\r Customer\r     Yes / One \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Container for the billing or customer information.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/Customer/\r CustomerID\r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer ID link to requesting store.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/Customer/\r PrimaryName\r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer or company name.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/Customer/\r     Contact\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer   contact, used for mostly businesses.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     Customer/\r     Telephone1\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer telephone number 1.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     Customer/\r     Telephone2\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer telephone number 2, used for mostly businesses.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     Customer/\r     Fax\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer fax number, used for mostly businesses.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     Customer/\r     Email\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer e-mail address.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     Customer/\r     Website\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer website, used for mostly businesses.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/Customer/\r     Address1\r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer address line 1.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/Customer/\r     Address2\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer address line 2.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/Customer/\r     CityTown\r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer city or town.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/Customer/\r     StateProvince\r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer state, province or region.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/Customer/\r     PostalCode\r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 15\r     Customer zipcode or postalcode.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/Customer/\r     CountryCode\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     2\r     Customer 2 character ISO country code. If no country code is provided, the country code found in Company/My Company will be used. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     Customer/SalesGLAccount\r     No / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     0 to 15 \r     Sales/Income GL Account for this sales order. If left blank, the order of precedence will be:\r     1. The customer default account from the customer record, if defined.\r     2. The default account as defined in My Company.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     Customer/\r     TaxIDNumber\r     No / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     0 to 15 \r     Customer sales tax ID number. May also be used for resale number, FEIN, VAT license, etc.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     Customer/AccountNumber\r     No / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     0 to 15 \r     Customer account number.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     BillTo\r     No / One \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Container for the billing or customer information. If this container is not provided, the customer information will be used as the bill to information. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     BillTo/\r     PrimaryName\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer or company name.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     BillTo/\r     Contact\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer contact, used for mostly businesses.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     BillTo/\r     Address1\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer address line 1.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     BillTo/\r     Address2\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer address line 2.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     BillTo/\r     CityTown\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer city or town.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     BillTo/\r     StateProvince\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer state, province or region.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     BillTo/\r     PostalCode\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 15\r     Customer zipcode or postalcode.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     BillTo/\r     CountryCode\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     2\r     Customer ISO country code. If no country code is provided, the country code found in Company/My Company will be used. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo\r     No / One \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Container for the shipping information. If this container is not provided, the customer information will be used as the ship to information.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo/\r     PrimaryName\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer or company name.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo/\r     Contact\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer contact, used for mostly businesses.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo/\r     Address1\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer address line 1.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo/\r     Address2\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer address line 2.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo/\r     CityTown\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer city or town.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo/\r     StateProvince\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 32 \r     Customer state, province or region.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo/\r     PostalCode\r     *Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 15\r     Customer zipcode or postalcode.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo/\r     CountryCode\r     No / Zero or One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     2\r     Customer ISO country code. If no country code is provided, the country code found in Company/My Company will be used. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r OrderSummary/\r ShipTo/ \r DropShipIndicator\r \r     No / Zero or One \r     Empty\r     0\r     Flag indicating this order is to be drop shipped. True if this container is present, false otherwise. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     OrderSummary/\r     ShipTo/\r     BlindShipIndicator \r     No / Zero or One \r     Empty\r     0\r     Flag indicating this order is to be blind shipped. True if this container is present, false otherwise. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r ItemDetails\r     Yes / One to Many \r     Container\r     &nbsp;\r     Container tag for each line item in the sales order. \r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r SalesOrder/\r ItemDetails/\r ItemID\r     Yes / One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 15\r     SKU/UPC code for the line item.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     ItemDetails/\r     Description\r     No / Zero to One \r     Alpha-numeric\r     1 to 64 \r     Short description of the line item.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     ItemDetails/\r     Quantity\r     Yes / One \r     Numeric\r     Float\r     Quantity of the line item being ordered.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     ItemDetails/\r     UnitPrice\r     Yes / One \r     Numeric\r     Float\r     Unit price  of the line item being ordered.\r   \r   \r     SalesOrderEntry/\r     SalesOrder/\r     ItemDetails/\r     SalesTax\r     No / Zero to One \r     Numeric\r     Float\r     Sales tax  of the line item being ordered. This field must match one of the sales tax rates define in KSSBooks to properly alloate the tax to the proper tax authorities.\r   \r \r &nbsp;\r 4.2 Response Request Interface Specification\r *Yes - will be present if the container tag is present.\r \r   \r     Element (XMLPath) \r     Required/Cardinality\r     Type\r     Length\r     Description/Values\r   \r   \r     &nbsp;\r     &nbsp;\r     &nbsp;\r     &nbsp;\r     &nbsp;\r   \r \r &nbsp;\r 4.3 Examples\r 5.0 Programming Information\r 5.1 Access Request Interface Specification\r 5.2 Response Request Interface Specification\r 5.3 Examples\r 6.0 Appendices\r 6.1 Glossary\r 6.2 Return Status and Error Codes\r 6.3 Reference Tables\r 6.4 Frequently Asked Questions\r &nbsp;'),(126,127,'0','en_us','12.03','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch12-SoapXML/03-Customers/03-XMLCustomerHome.html','SOAP/XML.Receivables Interface','SOAP/XML Receivables Interface','SOAP/XML Receivables Interface\r \r \r \r \r SOAP/XML Receivables Interface\r KSSBooks has an SOAP/XML interface build in to support XML type transfers that allow data to be inserted into and generated from the system. This will allow interfaces to third party applications and data transfers. Current XML definitions exist for:\r Sales Orders\r Submit Sales Orders (Import)\r Sales Invoices \r &nbsp;\r Future Definitions\r Generate Sales Order\r Cancel Sales Order\r Status Sales Order\r Invoice Sales Order\r Update Sales Order\r Submit Sales Invoice\r   Update Sales Invoice\r   Ship Sales Invoice\r   Status Sales Invoice'),(127,0,'0','en_us','12','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch12-SoapXML/XMLHome.html','SOAP/XML Interface','SOAP/XML Interface','SOAP/XML Interface\r \r \r \r \r SOAP/XML Interface\r KSSBooks has an SOAP/XML interface build in to support XML type transfers that allow data to be inserted into and generated from the system. This will allow interfaces to third party applications and data transfers. Current XML definitions exist for:\r Receivables\r Sales Orders (Import)\r Payables\r &nbsp;\r Inventory\r   Inventory (Export)'),(128,0,'d','en_us','13','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch13-ErrorMessages/ErrorMsgHome.html','Error Messages','Error Messages','Error Messages     Error Messages &nbsp;'),(129,0,'d','en_us','20','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/ch20-Glossary/GlossaryHome.html','Glossary','Glossary','Glossary     Glossary &nbsp;'),(130,0,'d','en_us','00','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/welcome.html','Help.Home','Welcome to KSSBooks','Welcome to KSSBooks\r \r \r \r \r Welcome to KSSBooks\r KSSBooks is an open source accounting application designed for ease of use and robust functionality. Written in freely available PHP and MySQL, KSSBooks has been tested on multiple platforms and browsers to ensure the broadest compatibility possible. \r Some of the feature highlights are:\r \r    Web based interface\r   Full featured accounting engine\r   Complete inventory control including assemblies\r   Multiple company capablility\r    Multiple language capablility\r    Robust reporting capability \r   Full featured import/export capability\r   User friendly installation and setup script\r   Extensive user level security \r \r KSSBooks is release under the GNU license.\r &nbsp;'),(131,0,'d','en_us','00','modules/kss/language/en_us/manual/welcome.php','Help.Home','Welcome to KSSBooks','Welcome to KSSBooks\r \r \r \r \r Welcome to KSSBooks\r KSSBooks is an open source accounting application designed for ease of use and robust functionality. Written in freely available PHP and MySQL, KSSBooks has been tested on multiple platforms and browsers to ensure the broadest compatibility possible. \r Some of the feature highlights are:\r \r    Web based interface\r   Full featured accounting engine\r   Complete inventory control including assemblies\r   Multiple company capablility\r    Multiple language capablility\r    Robust reporting capability \r   Full featured import/export capability\r   User friendly installation and setup script\r   Extensive user level security \r \r KSSBooks is release under the GNU license.\r &nbsp;'),(132,136,'d','en_us','07.04.01.01','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/01-Maintenance/01-AddItem.html','Inventory.Adding','Inventory - Adding Inventory','Inventory - Adding Inventory\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Adding Inventory \r Inventory items represent the goods and services produced, bought, contracted or consumed by your company. KSSBooks offers several inventory types to help manage the various attributes of each item. Some inventory types are tracked in your companies stock (stock items, master-stock items, assemblies) while others are not. All but the documentation type affect your companies financial position.\r To better help organize your inventory items, KSSBooks has a built in category and field tool. Attributes of inventory items can be added to category groups which can then be used in reports, forms, imported, exported or transfered to interface third party applications. For example, a category named packaging may be added to the inventory items and fields for package length, width, height and weight may be added to the category. \r HINT: Before creating inventory items, setting up inventory categories and fields is recommended. If the categories and fields  are set up prior to copying inventory items, the new fields will be copied when the item is copied saving the time to re-enter the data.\r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Edit/Maintain.\r   At the bottom of the list click New.\r   Enter the SKU number for the item to create and select the inventory type form the pull down menu.\r     \r   NOTE: Duplicate SKUs are not permitted. If a SKU is entered that is already in the system, an error will be displayed and the new SKU will not be created.\r   \r    Press New to create the SKU and continue to the next screen.\r     \r   Depending on the inventory type and number of categories defined, the tabs displayed on the data entry screen will vary. The first tab and will be the System tab. If the inventory type is an assembly, the second tab will show the Bill of Materials and is used to enter the sku\'s used to make up the assembly. The remaining tabs are user defined and are ordered as defined in the inventory categories set up menu. \r   \r   Enter the information for the item. Use the tabs to select each category type and enter fields for that particular category.\r   When all desired fields have been entered, press Save to save your information and return to the inventory edit/maintain window. \r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r Setting inventory default accounts\r   Editing inventory items\r   Copying inventory items\r   Deleting inventory items\r   Inventory adjustments\r   Entering an inventory assembly\r   Adding an inventory field\r   Editing an inventory field \r   Deleting an inventory field\r   Adding an inventory field tab (category)\r   Editing an inventory field tab (category)\r   Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r Inventory Activities \r Using the price manager  \r   Importing Inventory\r   Exporting inventory\r   Synchronizing with other applications\r Reports\r Inventory item list\r   Inventory assembly list \r   Inventory adjustment journal\r   Inventory assembly journal'),(133,136,'d','en_us','07.04.01.02','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/01-Maintenance/02-EditItem.html','Inventory.Editing','Inventory - Editing Inventory','Inventory - Editing Inventory\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Editing Inventory \r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Edit/Maintain.\r   The inventory item list screen will appear initially sorted by SKU. To locate the item you wish to edit, navigate by clicking on the sorting selection in the table head or enter a search criteria in the search box and press the Enter key on your keyboard. \r   Once you locate the item to edit, click on the edit icon  to advance to the date entry screen. \r     \r     Depending on the inventory type and number of categories defined, the tabs displayed on the data entry screen will vary. The first tab and will be the System tab. If the inventory type is an assembly, the second tab will show the Bill of Materials and is used to enter the skus used to make up the assembly. The remaining tabs are user defined and are ordered as defined in the inventory categories set up menu. \r   \r   Enter the information for the item. Use the tabs to select each category type and enter fields for that particular category.\r     \r     Note: Some fields may not be editable once certain journal entries have been made. For example, the cost method will be locked out once that item has been used in for a journal activity. Other fields are system maintained and cannot be changed. These fields are either read only or disabled and cannot be changed on the form. \r   \r   When all desired fields have been entered, press Update to save your information and return to the inventory edit/maintain window.\r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r Setting inventory default accounts\r   Adding inventory items\r   Copying inventory items\r   Deleting inventory items \r   Inventory adjustments\r   Entering an inventory assembly\r   Adding an inventory field\r   Editing an inventory field \r   Deleting an inventory field\r   Adding an inventory field tab (category)\r   Editing an inventory field tab (category)\r   Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r Inventory Activities \r Using the price manager\r   Importing Inventory\r   Exporting inventory\r   Synchronizing with other applications\r Reports\r Inventory item list\r   Inventory assembly list \r   Inventory adjustment journal\r   Inventory assembly journal'),(134,136,'d','en_us','07.04.01.03','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/01-Maintenance/03-CopyItem.html','Inventory.Copying','Inventory - Copying Inventory','Inventory - Copying Inventory\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Copying Inventory \r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Edit/Maintain.\r   The inventory item list screen will appear initially sorted by SKU. To locate the item you wish to copy, navigate by clicking on the sorting selection in the table head or enter a search criteria in the search box and press the Enter key on your keyboard. \r   Once you locate the item to copy, click on the copy icon  and a popup window will appear requesting a SKU for the new item.\r   Enter the new SKU into the field and press OK to advance to the data entry screen. Most of the fields from the source item will be copied to the new item and will be shown on the form. Certain system items, such as quantity on hand, quantity on order, quantity on sales order will not be copied over and these fields will be initially set to zero. \r     \r     Depending on the inventory type and number of categories defined, the tabs displayed on the data entry screen will vary. The first tab and will be the System tab. If the inventory type is an assembly, the second tab will show the Bill of Materials and is used to enter the sku\'s used to make up the assembly. The remaining tabs are user defined and are ordered as defined in the inventory categories set up menu. \r   \r   Enter/change the information for the newly copied item. Use the tabs to select each category type and enter fields for that particular category.\r     \r     Note: Some fields may not be editable once certain journal entries have been made. For example, the cost method will be locked out once that item has been used in for a journal activity. Other fields are system maintained and cannot be changed. These fields are either read only or disabled and cannot be changed on the form. \r   \r   When all desired fields have been entered, press Update to save your information and return to the inventory edit/maintain window.\r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r Setting inventory default accounts\r   Adding inventory items\r   Editing inventory items \r   Deleting inventory items \r   Inventory adjustments\r   Entering an inventory assembly\r   Adding an inventory field\r   Editing an inventory field \r   Deleting an inventory field\r   Adding an inventory field tab (category)\r   Editing an inventory field tab (category)\r   Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r Inventory Activities \r Using the price manager\r   Importing Inventory\r   Exporting inventory\r   Synchronizing with other applications\r Reports\r Inventory item list\r   Inventory assembly list \r   Inventory adjustment journal\r   Inventory assembly journal'),(135,136,'d','en_us','07.04.01.04','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/01-Maintenance/04-DeleteItem.html','Inventory.Deleting','Inventory - Deleting Inventory','Inventory - Deleting Inventory\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Deleting Inventory \r Note: An inventory item cannot be deleted if there are journal entries posted with the item. If the user tries to delete an item that has been posted to the journal, an error will be displayed and the item will not be deleted. Once all journal entries related to this item have been removed, the item can be deleted. If this is not possible, consider marking the SKU as inactive.\r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Edit/Maintain.\r   The inventory item list screen will appear initially sorted by SKU. To locate the item you wish to edit, navigate by clicking on the sorting selection in the table head or enter a search criteria in the search box and press the Enter key on your keyboard. \r   Once you locate the item to edit, click on the delete icon   and a popup window will appear confirming the delete operation.\r   Click OK to confirm the delete operation and the item will be removed from the database.\r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r Setting inventory default accounts\r   Adding inventory items\r   Editing inventory items \r   Copying inventory items\r   Inventory adjustments\r   Entering an inventory assembly\r   Adding an inventory field\r   Editing an inventory field \r   Deleting an inventory field\r   Adding an inventory field tab (category)\r   Editing an inventory field tab (category)\r   Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r Inventory Activities \r Using the price manager\r   Importing Inventory\r   Exporting inventory\r   Synchronizing with other applications\r Reports\r Inventory item list\r   Inventory assembly list \r   Inventory adjustment journal\r   Inventory assembly journal'),(136,149,'0','en_us','07.04.01','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/01-Maintenance/MaintenanceHome.html','Inventory.Maintenance','Inventory - Maintenance','Inventory - Maintenance\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Maintenance\r Inventory items represent the goods and services produced, bought, contracted or consumed by your company. KSSBooks offers several inventory types to help manage the various attributes of each item. Some inventory types are tracked in your companies stock (stock items, master-stock items, assemblies) while others are not. All but the documentation type affect your companies financial position.\r To better help organize your inventory items, KSSBooks has a built in category and field tool. Attributes of inventory items can be added to category groups which can then be used in reports, forms, imported, exported or transfered to interface third party applications. For example, a category named packaging may be added to the inventory items and fields for package length, width, height and weight may be added to the category. \r HINT: Before creating inventory items, setting up inventory categories and fields is recommended. If the categories and fields  are set up prior to copying inventory items, the new fields will be copied when the item is copied saving the time to re-enter the data.\r Related Topics\r Inventory\r Setting inventory default accounts\r   Adding inventory items\r   Editing inventory items\r   Copying inventory items\r   Deleting inventory items\r   Inventory adjustments\r   Entering an inventory assembly\r   Adding an inventory field\r   Editing an inventory field \r   Deleting an inventory field\r   Adding an inventory field tab (category)\r   Editing an inventory field tab (category)\r   Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r Inventory Activities \r Using the price manager  \r  Importing Inventory\r   Exporting inventory\r   Synchronizing with other applications'),(137,139,'d','en_us','07.04.02.01','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/02-Adjustments/01-AdjustmentEdit.html','Inventory.Adjustments - Edit','Inventory - Adjustments (Edit)','Inventory - Adjustments (Edit)\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Adjustments (Edit) \r Edit inventory adjustment procedure \r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Adjustments.\r   Press the Open button to display the inventory adjustment popup window. \r   Select the adjustment to edit by clicking anywhere on the row of the adjustment.\r   Change any fields as necessary. \r   Press Save to post the transaction to the journal. Note: Editing a journal entry first un-posts the original transaction and re-posts with the new data. Cost of good sold will be recalculated based on the post date of the edited adjustment. \r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r     Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Deleting inventory items \r     Inventory adjustment\r     Deleting an inventory adjustment\r     \r   Inventory assemblies\r   Adding an inventory field\r   Editing an inventory field\r   Deleting an inventory field\r   Adding an inventory category \r   Editing an inventory category \r Deleting an inventory category\r &nbsp;'),(138,139,'d','en_us','07.04.02.02','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/02-Adjustments/02-AdjustmentDelete.html','Inventory.Adjustments - Delete','Inventory - Adjustments (Delete)','Inventory - Adjustments (Delete)\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Adjustments (Delete) \r Delete inventory adjustment procedure \r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Adjustments.\r   Press the Open button to display the inventory adjustment popup window. \r   Select the adjustment to delete by clicking anywhere on the row of the adjustment.\r   Press the Delete button and confirm you selection to un-post the transaction from the journal.\r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r Setting inventory default accounts\r     Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Deleting inventory items \r     Inventory adjustments\r     Edit an inventory adjustment\r      \r   Inventory assemblies\r   Adding an inventory field\r   Editing an inventory field\r   Deleting an inventory field\r   Adding an inventory category \r   Editing an inventory category \r Deleting an inventory category\r &nbsp;'),(139,149,'0','en_us','07.04.02','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/02-Adjustments/AdjustmentsHome.html','Inventory.Adjustments','Inventory - Adjustments','Inventory - Adjustments\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Adjustments\r Inventory adjustments are necessary when your physical inventory stock  counts do not match the calculated count within KSSBooks. An inventory adjustment will be necessary to synchronize KSSBooks with physical inventory. The two possible adjustments are increase in inventory (less physical inventory on hand than expected) and reduce inventory (more physical inventory on hand than expected). \r Inventory adjustment procedure \r  Inventory shortages can occur form many ways. Pilferage, damage, loss are a few. The stock counts within KSSBooks will need to be adjusted to match the actual stock on hand. \r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Adjustments.\r   Enter the SKU or a search criteria and press the open icon  . \r   Select the SKU to adjust from the popup menu to fill in the item attributes (or if there is only one match, the popup window will close and fill in the necessary information).\r   Enter a reference for this transaction (i.e. ADJ2007-05-12).\r   Enter the post date of the adjustment or use the popup calendar to select a post date. Today\'s date is loaded by default. \r   Select the GL account popup icon  and select the account to apply the adjustment. \r   Enter the total cost of the adjustment. This value only applies to increases in inventory. For inventory decreases, the cost field is ignored and the cost is calculated by KSSBooks using the items cost method and historical purchase prices.\r   Enter the adjustment quantity.\r   Enter a reason for adjustment. (i.e. damaged, expired, etc.) \r   Press Save to post the transaction to the journal. \r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r Setting inventory default accounts\r     Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Deleting inventory items\r     Edit an inventory adjustment\r     Deleting an inventory adjustment\r     Inventory assemblies\r     Adding an inventory field\r     Editing an inventory field \r     Deleting an inventory field\r     Adding an inventory field tab (category)\r     Editing an inventory field tab (category)\r     Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r &nbsp;'),(140,142,'d','en_us','07.04.03.01','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/03-Assemblies/01-AssembliesEdit.html','Inventory.Assemblies - Edit','Inventory - Assemblies (Edit)','Inventory - Assemblies (Edit)\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Assemblies (Edit) \r Edit inventory adjustment procedure \r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Assemblies.\r   Press the Open button to display the inventory assemblies popup window. \r   Select the assembly to edit by clicking anywhere on the row of the assembly.\r   Change any fields as necessary. \r   Press Save to post the transaction to the journal. Note: Editing a journal entry first un-posts the original transaction and re-posts with the new data. Cost of good sold will be recalculated based on the post date of the edited adjustment.\r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r  Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Deleting inventory items\r     Inventory adjustments\r     Inventory assemblies - Delete\r     Inventory assemblies   \r     Adding an inventory field\r     Editing an inventory field\r     Deleting an inventory field\r     Adding Inventory field tabs (categories)\r     Editing an inventory field tab (category) \r     Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r &nbsp;'),(141,142,'d','en_us','07.04.03.02','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/03-Assemblies/02-AssembliesDelete.html','Inventory.Assemblies - Delete','Inventory - Assemblies (Delete)','Inventory - Assemblies (Delete)\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Assemblies (Delete)\r Delete inventory assembly procedure \r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Assemblies.\r   Press the Open button to display the inventory assembly popup window. \r   Select the assembly to delete by clicking anywhere on the row of the adjustment.\r   Press the Delete button and  confirm you selection to un-post the transaction from the journal.\r \r &nbsp;\r Related Topics\r Inventory\r  Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Deleting inventory items \r     Inventory adjustments\r     Inventory assemblies   \r     Inventory assemblies - Edit\r     Inventory assemblies - Delete     \r     Adding an inventory field\r     Editing an inventory field\r     Deleting an inventory field\r     Adding Inventory field tabs (categories)\r     Editing an inventory field tab (category) \r     Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r &nbsp;'),(142,149,'0','en_us','07.04.03','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/03-Assemblies/AssembliesHome.html','Inventory.Assemblies','Inventory - Assemblies','Inventory - Assemblies\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Assemblies\r Inventory assemblies are inventory items that are comprised of one or more other inventory items. When an inventory item is created, the inventory type is selected at the time the SKU is entered to identify the characteristics of the item. When the assembly type is selected the item is assumed to be made up with other items from the inventory database. In order to sell an assembly type item, it must be assembled in KSSBooks to show stock on hand. Note that an assembled item may also be purchased directly in which case inventory will show stock but no assemblies were necessary. \r Inventory assembly procedure \r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Assemblies.\r   Enter the SKU or a search criteria and press the open icon . Note: Only inventory items of type \'assembly\' will be displayed in the popup.\r   Select the SKU to assemble from the popup menu to fill in the item attributes (or if there is only one match, the popup window will close and fill in the necessary information). A list will be displayed of the required items and quantities needed to assemble the item and shortages will be displayed in red.\r   Enter a reference for this transaction (i.e. ADJ2007-05-12).\r   Enter the post date of the adjustment or use the popup calendar to select a post date. Today\'s date is loaded by default. \r   Enter the total number of units to assemble. After the number of units to assemble is entered, KSSBooks calculates the number of required  items to build the requested amount and will warn if there are not enough pieces to build.\r   Press Save to post the transaction to the journal. \r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r  Inventory assemblies - Edit\r     Inventory assemblies - Delete\r     Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Deleting inventory items\r     Inventory adjustments - Adding \r     Adding an inventory field\r     Editing an inventory field\r     Deleting an inventory field\r     Adding Inventory field tabs (categories)\r     Editing an inventory field tab (category) \r     Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r &nbsp;'),(143,145,'d','en_us','07.04.04.01','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/04-Tabs/01-TabsEdit.html','Inventory.Tabs - Edit','Inventory - Tabs (Category) (Edit)','Inventory - Tabs (Category) (Edit)\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Tabs (Category) (Edit)\r Editing an Inventory Tab (Category)\r \r   From the main menu select Inventory-&gt;Setup Inventory Field Tabs.\r   Click anywhere on the row to highlight.\r   Press the Edit button. \r   Edit the inventory tab fields. \r   Press Update to save your changes. \r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r  Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Inventory adjustments\r     Inventory tabs (categories)\r     Deleting an inventory tab (category)\r     Inventory fields\r     Editing an inventory field\r     Deleting an inventory field\r Import/Export\r Importing Inventory\r   Exporting inventory\r &nbsp;'),(144,145,'d','en_us','07.04.04.02','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/04-Tabs/02-TabsDelete.html','Inventory.Tabs - Delete','Inventory - Tabs (Category) (Delete)','Inventory - Tabs (Category) (Delete)\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Tabs (Category) (Delete)\r WARNING: Deleting a tab will also delete all inventory fields that are part of that tab. To keep the fields, edit each inventory field and reassign them to a valid tab before deleting.\r Deleting an Inventory tab (category)\r \r   From the main menu select Inventory-&gt;Setup Inventory Field Tabs.\r   Click anywhere on the row to highlight.\r   Press the Edit button. \r   Edit the inventory tab fields. \r   Press the Delete button to delete and a confirmation will appear.\r   Press the Delete button on the confirmation to delete the tab.\r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r  Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Inventory adjustments\r     Inventory tabs (categories)\r     Editing an inventory tab (category) \r     Inventory fields\r     Editing an inventory field\r     Deleting an inventory field\r Import/Export\r Importing Inventory\r   Exporting inventory\r &nbsp;'),(145,149,'0','en_us','07.04.04','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/04-Tabs/TabsHome.html','Inventory.Tabs','Inventory - Tabs (Categories)','Inventory - Tabs (Categories)\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Tabs (Categories)\r KSSBooks has a built in feature to expand inventory attributes (fields) to allow for further refinement of your inventory items.  To help organize these expanded fields, added inventory fields are organized into categories. These categories become the tab headings when maintaining your inventory items. The mandatory inventory fields are, by default, put into the \'System\' tab. If the inventory type is an assembly, a second tab name \'Bill of Materials\' is also added. At least one tab must be added before inventory fields can be entered.\r Adding an Inventory Tab (Category)\r \r   From the main menu select Inventory-&gt;Setup Inventory Field Tabs.\r   Press the New button.\r   Enter a short name for the inventory tab, 10 characters or less, no spaces.\r   Enter the sort position. This will determine the display order of the tabs when maintaining inventory items.\r   Enter a tab description. This field will show up below the tab to describe the contents of the tab. \r   Press Insert to add the new tab. \r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r  Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Inventory adjustments\r     Editing an inventory tab (category)\r     Deleting an inventory tab (category)\r     Add inventory fields\r     Editing an inventory field\r     Deleting an inventory field\r Import/Export\r Importing Inventory\r Exporting inventory\r &nbsp;'),(146,148,'d','en_us','07.04.05.01','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/05-Fields/01-FieldsEdit.html','Inventory.Custom Fields - Edit','Inventory - Custom Fields (Edit)','Inventory - Custom Fields (Edit)\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Custom Fields (Edit)\r Editing a Custom Inventory Field \r \r   From the main menu select Inventory-&gt;Setup Inventory Fields.\r   Click anywhere on the row to highlight.\r   Press the Edit button. \r   Edit the custom inventory fields. \r   Press Update to save your changes.\r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r  Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Inventory adjustments\r     Inventory field tabs (categories)\r     Editing an inventory field tab (category) \r     Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r     Adding an inventory field\r     Deleting an inventory field\r Import/Export\r Importing Inventory\r   Exporting inventory\r &nbsp;'),(147,148,'d','en_us','07.04.05.02','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/05-Fields/02-FieldsDelete.html','Inventory.Custom Fields - Delete','Inventory - Custom Fields (Delete)','Inventory - Custom Fields (Delete)\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Custom Fields (Delete)\r WARNING: Deleting a inventory custom field will delete all inventory information stored in the targeted field. This action is not reversible. \r Deleting an Inventory Custom Field\r \r   From the main menu select Inventory-&gt;Setup Inventory Fields.\r   Click anywhere on the row to highlight.\r   Press the Edit button. \r   Press the Delete button to delete and a confirmation will appear.\r   Press the Delete button on the confirmation to delete the custom field.\r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r  Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Inventory adjustments\r     Inventory field tabs (categories)\r     Editing an inventory field tab (category) \r     Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r     Inventory fields\r     Editing an inventory field\r Import/Export\r Importing Inventory\r   Exporting inventory\r &nbsp;'),(148,149,'0','en_us','07.04.05','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/05-Fields/FieldsHome.html','Inventory.Custom Fields','Inventory - Custom Fields','Inventory - Custom Fields\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Custom Fields\r KSSBooks has a built in feature to expand inventory fields (attributes) to allow for further refinement of your inventory items. To help organize these expanded fields, added inventory fields are organized into categories. These categories become the tab headings when maintaining your inventory items. The mandatory inventory fields are, by default, put into the \'System\' category (tab). If the inventory type is an assembly, a second tab name \'Bill of Materials\' is also added. At least one category must be added before inventory fields can be entered. As many fields can be added to a category as are needed. \r Adding an Inventory Field\r \r   From the main menu select Inventory-&gt;Setup Inventory Fields.\r   Press the New button.\r   Enter a short name for the inventory field name, 10 characters or less, no spaces. This field must be compatible with the database naming convention. (mysql, etc.) \r   Enter a description. This is the field that will generally be used when maintaining inventory.\r   Select the category to place this field into. This will determine what tab heading the field will appear when inventory items are edited.\r   Enter the field type and properties. On some fields, default properties may be entered to pre-define the field when a new item is entered. \r   Press New to add the new inventory field.\r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r  Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Delete inventory items\r     Inventory adjustments\r     Inventory field tabs (categories)\r     Editing an inventory field tab (category) \r     Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r     Editing an inventory field \r     Deleting an inventory field\r Import/Export\r Importing Inventory\r   Exporting inventory\r &nbsp;'),(149,175,'0','en_us','07.04','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/InventoryHome.html','Inventory','Inventory Home','Inventory Home\r \r \r \r \r Inventory\r KSSBooks uses inventory to represent all items, activities, and services your company offers to its customers. \r Inventory types include:\r Stock - Represents items that are stocked by your company. This includes items that are purchased and re-sold by your company without any value-added provided by your company. Retail type companies typically use stock type items. Stock item movement and cost is tracked in the general ledger. \r Master-Stock - Master-stock items are items that contain attributes associated with the item. For example, a shirt item would have the attributes size and color associated with each item. kssbooks will assign a unique item id to each variation to track inventory activity of each size/color item but retain the link to the master stock item for reporting activity. Master-stock item movement and cost is tracked in the general ledger. \r Serialized - Serialized items are items that are assembled and sold  by an unique serial number. Serialized item movement and cost are tracked in the general ledger. \r Assemblies - Item assemblies consist of one or more inventory items grouped together and sold as an individual item. This inventory type can also be used to group items sold as packages. Assembly item movement and cost is tracked in the general ledger. \r Non-stock - Non-stock items are physical items whose costs are not tracked in the general ledger. They may include supplies, packaging material, assembly materials, etc. \r Labor - Labor items are associated with employee chargeable time. Labor may be applied to either internal work order activities as well as labor charges to customer for services performed. Labor is typically charged by a time unit (hourly, daily, etc).\r Service - Service items are items that typically represent a fixed charged for a service. For example, a packaging charge or handling would be a service. Service costs are tracked in the general ledger. \r Charge - A charge item would be a fixed price charge for materials and/or services. Shop supplies and disposal fees would be examples of charges. Charge item costs are tracked in the general ledger. \r Activity - \r Description - This is a text only item used to communicate information. No cost or activity is tracked in the general ledger. The description item would be typically used for standard statements included with purchase orders, sales orders, etc. \r Inventory Categories\r kssbooks uses system and company categories to organize inventory characteristics. A default tab for system required fields cannot be edited or deleted. A second tab will be displayed for assembly type inventory items. Additional tabs may be added by the company to help further define the characteristics of their inventory items. For example, additional tabs may be added to include product dimensions, shipping properties, application descriptions, etc. \r Inventory Fields\r KSSBooks allows additional fields to be entered to the inventory database table. This allows customized inventory characteristics to be added to fit your companies needs. Inventory field types include text, HTML, hyperlinks, image paths, inventory links, integers and floating point numbers, dates and times, drop-down menus radio buttons and checkboxes. Refer to the section on inventory fields for more information. \r Related Topics\r User and Security Settings\r Setting user access security\r Inventory Activities \r  Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Delete inventory items\r     Entering an inventory assembly\r Inventory Categories\r  Add inventory field tabs (categories)\r     Editing an inventory field tab (category) \r     Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r Inventory Fields \r Adding an inventory field\r    Editing and inventory field\r    Deleting an inventory field\r  General Ledger\r Setting up default inventory accounts \r   Adding, editing and deleting general ledger accounts \r Importing/Exporting\r Building an import/export map\r   Importing/Exporting data\r Reports\r &nbsp;'),(150,152,'d','en_us','07.05.01.01','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/05-Banking/01-Payments/01-SinglePayments.html','Banking.Single Payments','Banking - Single Payments','Banking - Single Payments\r \r \r \r \r Banking - Single Payments\r This procedure covers payments via check, eft, or other non-paper method to a single supplier. This method is best used when payment is desired to a single supplier as it allows for easier selection of the supplier of interest. Payments Ref Numbers cannot be duplicated in the system. \r To pay a bill to a single supplier - writing a check \r \r   From the menu click on Banking -&gt; Pay Bills.\r   Enter part of the supplier name to search for and press the open folder icon next to the supplier id field.\r   A popup will be displayed showing the suppliers that match the entered search criteria. NOTE: Only the suppliers that have an outstanding bill to be paid will be displayed. If the supplier is not listed, make sure there is an open invoice entered into KSSBooks to pay.\r   Click anywhere on the supplier name to fill in the Payments form and close the popup.\r   All outstanding invoices from this supplier will be displayed, including any open supplier credit memos. Click on the Pay checkbox next to all the invoices you wish to pay. If the supplier payment terms have been set, any early payment discounts will be calculated. They may also be entered manually (note that the balance is calculated automatically if a discount is entered).\r   Enter the Payment Ref #, this is usually the check number to be printed.\r    Enter the check date, Reference, and account information as necessary. \r   Press the Print icon to generate the form. The forms of type banking:checks will be displayed. Check the radio button of the form to print, select the delivery method and press the PDF icon. \r   Print to the pre-printed checks on the printer.\r \r The Payment Ref Num will be automatically incremented.\r To pay a bill via EFT, credit card, and other non-check methods \r \r   Follow the procedure above, except enter an unique Payment Ref that identifies the payment. Select the correct account and post the payment by clicking the Save icon. To pay by credit card, select a short term liability account to post the payment to. \r \r NOTE: After paying with this method, the Payment Ref Num will auto-increment, probably to something non-desirable. It will need to be re-entered (back to the next check num) when the next run of bills are paid by checks to the next check number.\r Related Topics\r Inventory\r Creating Inventory Items\r     Receiving Inventory \r Banking\r  Paying Bills - Single Payment\r     Paying Bills - Bulk Payment\r   Paying Bills with credit cards \r   Reconciling cash accounts \r Reports \r Bank Checks\r &nbsp;'),(151,152,'d','en_us','07.05.01.02','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/05-Banking/01-Payments/02-BulkPayments.html','Banking.Bulk Payments','Banking - Bulk Payments','Banking - Bulk Payments\r \r \r \r \r Banking - Bulk Payments\r This procedure covers payments via check, eft, or other non-paper method to one or more suppliers. This method is preferred for paying supplier invoices to multiple suppliers in a single operation. Payments Ref Numbers cannot be duplicated in the system but this procedure automatically increments the Payment Ref Numbers as each payment is generated. \r To pay a bill to multiple suppliers - writing a checks \r \r   From the menu click on Banking -&gt; Select for Payment. A list of invoices that are due today will be displayed. Grayed out invoices may be shown and are an indication of invoices that are due but do not have an invoice number assigned to them.\r   Select a date form the Invoices Due By and Discounts Lost By calendar selections and press the Search icon. \r   A new list of invoices that are due (or discounts lost) will be displayed. Select all of the invoice to pay in this batch by checking the Pay checkboxes next tot he invoices to pay or press the Pay All icon to have KSSBooks check all the boxes for you. Uncheck any invoices you don\'t want to pay. Discounts are automatically calculated and the balance of the cash account is calculated. \r   Enter the First Check Number, this is  the first check number to be printed. KSSBooks will automatically increment the check number as the check for each supplier is generated. \r    Enter the check date,  and gl account information as necessary. \r   Press the Print icon to generate the form. The forms of type banking:checks will be displayed. Check the radio button of the form to print, select the delivery method and press the PDF icon. \r   KSSBooks generates one check page for each supplier, combing all invoices from the same supplier into a single check. Print to the pre-printed checks on the printer (make sure the sequence is correct).\r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r Creating Inventory Items\r     Receiving Inventory \r Banking\r  Paying Bills - Single Payment\r     Paying Bills - Bulk Payment\r   Paying Bills with credit cards \r   Reconciling cash accounts \r Reports \r Bank Checks\r &nbsp;'),(152,157,'0','en_us','07.05.01','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/05-Banking/01-Payments/PaymentsHome.html','Banking.Payments','Banking - Payments','Banking - Payments\r \r \r \r \r Banking - Payments\r Bill Payments by Check - There are two ways to pay bills, individually or in bulk:\r  Paying Bills - Single Payment\r     Paying Bills - Bulk Payment\r &nbsp;'),(153,154,'d','en_us','07.05.02.01','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/05-Banking/02-Receipts/01-SingleReceipts.html','Banking.Customer Receipts','Banking - Customer Receipts','Banking - Customer Receipts\r \r \r \r \r Banking - Customer Receipts\r This procedure covers payments via check, eft, or other  method from a single customer. Receipt Ref Numbers are automatically generated by the system (but can be over-ridden) to group deposits together. Deposit reference numbers can be duplicated in the system. \r Receiving Payment from a Customer\r \r   Select Banking-&gt;Customer Receipts .\r    Enter the Customer ID or press the open icon next to the Customer ID field. A popup will appear only displaying the customers with outstanding invoices. \r    Select the customer that you received a payment from. The popup window will close and fill in the list of outstanding invoices on the receipts form.\r   Check the Pay box of the invoices you receive money from. Adjust the discount as necessary. \r   Use the pre-selected deposit reference number of enter a reference number in the Deposit  ID field.\r   Enter the date of the deposit (default is today).\r   Change the cash and discount accounts if necessary.\r   Select the Deposit method from the pull down menu. Payment receipt methods are determined by the payment modules installed. Every payment module has their own set of fields to enter. Fill in any necessary payment information.\r   Either Save or Print the payment. Saving is typically used for payments received where no receipt is necessary whereas printing is typically used for when a receipt is necessary (such as POS). The payment will be posted to the general ledger. \r \r To pay a bill via EFT, credit card, and other non-check methods \r \r   Follow the procedure above, except enter an unique Payment Ref that identifies the payment. Select the correct account and post the payment by clicking the Save icon.\r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r Creating Inventory Items\r     Receiving Inventory \r Banking\r  \r Reconciling cash accounts \r Viewing the balance of a cash account\r \r Reports \r Bank Checks\r   Deposit Slips \r &nbsp;'),(154,157,'0','en_us','07.05.02','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/05-Banking/02-Receipts/ReceiptsHome.html','Banking.Receipts','Banking - Receipts','Banking - Receipts\r \r \r \r \r Banking - Receipts\r When a customer submits a payment for an outstanding invoice, the banking receipts function is used. \r Receiving Payment from a Customer\r \r   Select Banking-&gt;Customer Receipts .\r    Enter the Customer ID or press the open icon next to the Customer ID field. A popup will appear only displaying the customers with outstanding invoices. \r    Select the customer that you received a payment from. The popup window will close and fill in the list of outstanding invoices on the Pay Bills form.\r   Check the Pay box of the invoices you wish to pay. Adjust the discount as necessary. \r   Enter a Reference Number in the Reference field.\r   Enter the check number in the Deposit Ticket ID field.\r   Enter the date of the check (default is today).\r   Change the cash and discount accounts if necessary.\r   Select the Payment Method from the pull down menu. Fill in any necessary payment information.\r   Either Save or Print the payment. Saving is typically used for payments received where no receipt is necessary whereas printing is typically used for when a receipt is necessary (such as POS). The payment will be posted to the general ledger. \r \r Related Topics\r Voiding a Receipt \r   Editing a Receipt \r   Deleting a Receipt \r &nbsp;'),(155,157,'d','en_us','07.05.03','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/05-Banking/03-BankRegister/RegisterHome.html','Banking.Cash Register','Banking - Cash Register','Banking - Cash Register\r \r \r \r \r Banking - Cash Register \r KSSBooks provides a view of the current status of your cash accounts. The register shows all deposits and withdrawals for a given accounting period, including future posted transactions.\r To View Your Cash Account\r \r   Select Banking -&gt; Bank Account Register.\r   The screen will display a beginning balance for the period and all transactions that were posted for the period. \r   To change cash accounts, select a new account from the GL Account pull down menu. \r \r Related Topics\r Reports\r Printing Deposit Slips \r Printing Bank Checks'),(156,157,'d','en_us','07.05.04','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/05-Banking/04-Reconcilliation/ReconcilliationHome.html','Banking.Account Reconciliation','Banking - Account Reconciliation','Banking - Account Reconciliation\r \r \r \r \r Banking - Account Reconciliation\r Account reconciliation balances the kssbooks cash account with your financial institution. \r Account Reconciliation\r \r   Open the account reconciliation screen by selecting Banking-&gt;Account Reconciliation.\r   Select the cash account to reconcile.\r   enter the ending balance in the Statement Ending Balance&nbsp;box. The unreconciled amount will appear in the Unreconciled Difference box. \r   Check the box next to the item as cleared that appear on you financial institutions statement. \r   After checking all cleared items, the Unreconciled difference should be zero. If not recheck you checked boxes with your statement and correct any errors.\r   Press the Save icon to save your changes.'),(157,175,'0','en_us','07.05','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/05-Banking/BankingHome.html','Banking','Banking Home','Banking Home\r \r \r \r \r Banking\r kssbooks tracks customer payments and payments to suppliers.  The following services are available in KSSBooks:\r Customer Receipts - Checks, credit cards, and EFTs from your customers.\r Supplier Payments - Checks, EFTs to you suppliers and service providers. \r \r Bank Account Reconciliation - Reconcile KSSBooks cash accounts with you financial institution.\r &nbsp;'),(158,161,'d','en_us','07.06.01','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/06-GenLedger/01-ChartOfAccounts/ChartHome.html','General Journal.Chart of Accounts','General Journal - Chart of Accounts','General Journal - Chart of Accounts\r \r \r \r \r General Journal - Chart of Accounts\r The chart of accounts is the key to a successful accounting application. kssbooks allow for accounts name that include characters as well as numbers. It also allows for sub-accounts to be used later in roll-up reporting. If you are not sure how to set up your chart of accounts, refer to your accountant or use one of the supplied chart of accounts during the set-up script.\r Notes: \r \r   Exactly one account of type \'Retained Earnings\' may be part of the chart of accounts.\r   Accounts cannot be deleted if they have been used in a journal entry.\r   Accounts should be checked as inactive if they are no longer used but have past journal entries against it.\r \r Adding a general ledger account\r \r   Select General Journal-&gt;Chart of Accounts.\r   Click on the New icon and a popup will appear.\r   Enter the GL account number (0-9 and a-z are allowed).\r   Enter the description, and subaccount information as necessary.\r   Enter the Account Type. This classifies the account and how entries are treated in the general journal.\r   Press Save to create the account and close the window.\r \r Deleting a general ledger account\r \r   Select General Journal-&gt;Chart of Accounts.\r   Click the Delete icon next to the account to be deleted.\r   Acknowledge the deletion and the account will be removed.\r     NOTE: if the account has journal entries in the database, the account cannot be deleted.\r \r Editing a general ledger account\r \r   Select General Ledger-Chart of Accounts.\r   Click the edit icon next to the account to be edited. \r   Make any changes and press Save to commit your changes and close the window.\r     NOTE: Account numbers cannot be changed if they have a journal entry posted against it.\r \r Related Links\r General Journal Entries\r   Reports - Balance Sheet\r   Reports - Income Statement\r &nbsp;'),(159,161,'d','en_us','07.06.02','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/06-GenLedger/02-JournalEntries/JournalHome.html','General Journal.Journal Entries','General Journal - Journal Entries','General Journal - Journal Entries\r \r \r \r \r General Journal - Journal Entries\r Entries can be made directly into the general journal. However, most entries are handled in the background as through the system scripts.\r Notes:\r \r   The journal must be in balance before the entry can be posted.\r   The accounts selected must be a valid entry from the chart of accounts. \r \r Posting a general journal entry:\r \r   Select General Journal-&gt;Journal Entry.\r   Enter the general ledger account and a description of the entry. A popup window listing the chart of accounts. \r   Enter the amount of the journal entry.\r   Repeat steps 2-3 for all entries. Use the Add icon to add additional rows.\r   Verify the journal entries are in balance and press the Save icon to commit the changes.\r \r Editing a general journal entry: \r \r   Select General Journal-&gt;Journal Entry.\r   Select the Open icon and a popup window will appear listing the entries for the current period. Select the entry to be edited or use the search/period selection to search for entries outside of the current period..\r   Edit any fields as necessary.\r   Verify the journal entries are in balance and press the Save icon to commit the changes. This action will first un-post the prior entry and re-post with the new values. \r \r Deleting a general journal entry:\r \r   Select General Journal-&gt;Journal Entry.\r   Select the Open icon and a popup window will appear listing the entries for the current period. Select the entry to be edited or use the search/period selection to search for entries outside of the current period..\r   Press the delete Icon and after confirmation, the journal entry will be un-posted and removed from the database.\r \r Related Links\r Chart of Accounts\r   Reports - Balance Sheet\r Reports - Income Statement \r &nbsp; \r &nbsp;'),(160,161,'d','en_us','07.06.03','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/06-GenLedger/03-Utilities/UtilitiesHome.html','General Journal.Utilities','General Journal - Utilities','General Journal - Utilities\r \r \r \r \r General Journal - Utilities\r General Journal utilities provide administrative functions such as fiscal year setup, defining the current accounting period, setting up beginning balances and purging the database tables. Security should be restricted to the general journal utilities since significant damage to the company data can be had here. \r General Journal Utilities include:\r Accounting period change - Sets the current accounting period to a specified period. typically, this will need to be changed at the start of each accounting period as defined in the fiscal year.\r Fiscal Year setup, addition and change - the first fiscal year is set up through the setup script. This script allows for changes to any fiscal year and also generates the next fiscal year. \r NOTE: For performance reasons, it is best not to generate the next fiscal year until it is necessary. Every journal entry that affects the financial statement propagates through the remaining periods from the post date to the last period defined in the database. This results in extra queries to the database and slows down each posting.\r NOTE: Once an entry has been entered for a period, the fiscal year for that period and any earlier periods will be locked and cannot be deleted or changed.\r Beginning Balances - This utility assists in transferring information from other accounting systems into KSSBooks to retain continuity of financial reporting. Beginning balances set the trial balance accounts prior to period 1 (the default first accounting period). The beginning balance utility also allows for importing of inventory balances and valuation, customer accounts receivable, and supplier accounts payable.\r Database purge - THIS FUNCTION WILL DESTROY ALL THE JOURNAL ENTRIES AND BEGINNING BALANCES. It is included for test and evaluation purposes to quickly erase all journal entries and resets inventory balances to zero. It will not remove customers, suppliers, employees or other set-up settings.\r &nbsp;'),(161,175,'0','en_us','07.06','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/06-GenLedger/GLHome.html','General Ledger','General Ledger Home','General Ledger Home     General Ledger Home &nbsp;'),(162,172,'d','en_us','07.08.01','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/08-Setup/01-Languages/LanguagesHome.html','Setup.Languages','Setup - Languages','Setup - Languages\r \r \r \r \r Setup - Languages\r Kssbooks is designed for multi-language capability. The standard release includes translations for English (US). Language modules, as they come available, are available at the KSSBooks website. Prior to login, the directory /modules/general/language is read and all loaded language modules will appear in a drop down at login. Once a language is selected, it is stored in a session variable and will remain in effect unitl the user logs out.'),(163,172,'d','en_us','07.08.02','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/08-Setup/02-Currencies/CurrenciesHome.html','Setup.Currencies','Setup - Currencies','Setup - Currencies\r \r \r \r \r Setup - Currencies\r KSSBooks is designed to handle multiple currencies. the US Dollar is the default currency shipped with the standard release.\r Updating the exchange rate \r Exchange rates can be updated through two exchange servers, oanda and xe. Oanda is the primary server and xe is the backup server should oanda be down. \r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Currencies.\r   Press the Update Exchange Rate icon, . The exchange rat servers will be queried and the rates updated. \r \r Adding a Currency\r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Currencies.\r   Press the New icon and a popup will appear.\r   Select the Title of the currency, i.e. US Dollar, Euro, Yen, etc.\r    Enter the ISO code for the currency, USD, EUR, etc.\r    Enter the symbol to use to the left and/or right, $ for USD, &euro; for EUR, etc. \r   Enter the symbol to use for the thousands place and decimal places.\r   Enter the current exchange rate relative to the default currency. Leave the value blank if it will be updated when the exchange rate is updated.\r   If this is to be the default currency, check the Set as Default box. \r   Press the Save icon to save the entry into the database.\r   Press the Update Exchange Rate icon to refresh the current exchange rate with the exchange rate servers. \r \r Changing the Default Currency\r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Currencies.\r   Press the Edit icon next to the currency to set as default and a popup will appear.\r   Check the Set as Default box. \r   Press the Save icon to save the entry into the database.\r \r Deleteing a Currency\r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Currencies.\r   Press the Delete icon next to the currency to delete and a confirmation popup will appear.\r   Press OK to confirm the deletion and the currency will be removed from the database. \r \r Related Links\r &nbsp;'),(164,166,'d','en_us','07.08.03.01','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/08-Setup/03-SalesTax/01-TaxAuthorities.html','Setup.Sales Tax Authorities','Setup - Sales Tax Authorities','Setup - Sales Tax Authorities\r \r \r \r \r Setup - Sales Tax Authorities\r Sales tax authorities can be set for one or more Tax Authorities. they can be assigned a different collection account to help facilitate tracking and payment of taxes collected. Sales tax authorities need to be set up prior to setting up sales tax rates.\r Adding a Sales Tax Authority\r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Sales Tax Authorities.\r   Press the New icon. A popup will appear with a form to fill out.\r   Enter a short name for the taxing authority, e.g. state tax, city tax, vat, etc.\r   Enter a more detailed description of the taxing authority.\r   Enter the general ledger account to track taxes collected for this authority.\r    If the supplier is in the database, select the supplier to use to send payment to when submitting the taxes to the authority.\r    Enter the tax rate in percent, e.g. 7.2, 15.0, etc. Use a decimal point (.) for non-integer percentages.\r   Press the Save icon to add the sales tax authority to the database.\r \r Editing a Sales Tax Authority\r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Sales Tax Authorities.\r   Press the Edit icon next to the sales tax authority to edit. A popup will appear with a form pre-filled with the current data.\r   Make any necessary changes and press the Save icon to update the sales tax authority in the database.\r   \r Deleting a Sales Tax Authority\r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Sales Tax Authorities.\r   Press the Delete icon next to the sales tax authority to Delete. A confirmation popup will appear.\r   Press OK to confirm the deletion and the sales tax authority will be removed from the  database.\r \r Related Links\r Sales Tax Overview\r   Sales Tax Rates \r Adding a Supplier Account\r   Adding a General Ledger Account'),(165,166,'d','en_us','07.08.03.02','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/08-Setup/03-SalesTax/02-TaxRates.html','Setup.Sales Tax Rates','Setup - Sales Tax Rates','Setup - Sales Tax Rates\r \r \r \r \r Setup - Sales Tax Rates\r Sales tax rates can be set at several levels depending on the taxing structure of your business. Prior to setting up sales tax rates, sales tax authorities need to be set up. Refer the the help file on Sales Tax Authorities for more information.\r Adding a Sales Tax Rate\r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Sales Tax Rates.\r   Press the New icon. A popup will appear with a form to fill out.\r   Enter a short name for the tax rate, e.g. Local Tax, State TAX, VAT, etc.\r   Enter a more detailed description of the tax rate.\r   To add or delete a taxing authority, select it from the appropriate list. NOTE: Only one authority can be added or removed at this time. To add more than one authority, save the entry and then edit it to add more. \r   If freight is taxable, selct the Yes radio box. \r   Press the Save icon to commit the entry to the database. \r \r Editing a Sales Tax Rate\r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Sales Tax Rates.\r   Press the Edit icon next to the sales tax rate to edit. A popup will appear with a form filled out with the current tax rate information.\r   Edit the short name or description as necessary.\r   To add or delete a taxing authority, select it from the appropriate list. NOTE: Only one authority can be added or removed at this time. To add more than one authority, save the entry and then edit it to add or remove another authority. \r   If freight is taxable, selct the Yes radio box. \r   Press the Save icon to commit the change to the database.\r \r Deleting a Sales Tax Rate\r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Sales Tax Rates.\r   Press the Delete icon next to the sales tax rate to delete. A confirmation popup will appear to verfiy the delete request.\r   Press OK to remove the sales tax rate from the database.\r \r Related Links\r Sales Tax Overview\r   Sales Tax Authorities'),(166,172,'0','en_us','07.08.03','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/08-Setup/03-SalesTax/SalesTaxHome.html','Setup.Sales Tax','Setup - Sales Tax','Setup - Sales Tax\r \r \r \r \r Setup - Sales Tax\r KSSBooks has a multilevel sales tax rate calculator built in. Sales tax is comprised of Tax Authorities and Tax Rates. Tax authorities are defined as the agencies that collect the tax and tax rates are a collection of one or more authorities. \r Kssbooks inventory items can be individually set as taxable or non-taxable. When an order is placed, one sales tax rate is applied to the entire order, but will not be calculated if the inventory item is tagged as non-taxable. For example, if a labor item is included in the invoice and is not taxable, it shouldbe flagged as non-taxable in the inventory database and thus will not be included in the sales tax calculation for the invoice. \r See the links below for detailed information on setting up, managing and removing sales tax authorities and rates. \r Related Links \r Sales Tax Authorities\r Sales Tax Rates'),(167,172,'d','en_us','07.08.04','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/08-Setup/04-Branches/BranchesHome.html','Setup.Company Warehouses','Setup - Company Warehouses','Setup - Company Warehouses\r \r \r \r \r Setup - Company Warehouses\r &nbsp;'),(168,170,'d','en_us','07.08.06.01','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/08-Setup/06-ImportExport/01-ImportData.html','Setup.Importing Data','Importing Data','Importing Data\r \r \r \r \r Importing Data\r Data can be imported into KSSBooks such as customers, suppliers, and inventory. \r The HOW TOs contain samples of import procedures to import customers, suppliers, and inventory.\r Related Links\r Importing/Exporting Overview\r   Exporting Data from KSSBooks'),(169,170,'d','en_us','07.08.06.02','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/08-Setup/06-ImportExport/02-ExportData.html','Setup.Exporting Data','Exporting Data','Exporting Data\r \r \r \r \r Exporting Data\r Data can be exported from KSSBooks to text files for use in other applications. \r The HOW TOs contain samples of export procedures to export customers, suppliers, and inventory.\r Related Links\r Importing/Exporting Overview\r   Importing Data into KSSBooks'),(170,172,'0','en_us','07.08.06','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/08-Setup/06-ImportExport/ImpExpHome.html','Setup.Importing Data','Importing/Exporting Data','Importing/Exporting Data\r \r \r \r \r Importing and Exporting Data\r KSSBooks has a powerful import/export tool to transfer data in to/out of the KSSBooks database. Knowledge of the KSSBooks database structure and data fields are necessary to acurately import information into the database. Exporting is less complicated but still required some knowledge of the database tables. \r Most import/export operations deal solely with a single database table. The exception is the account definitions (customers, suppliers, Warehouses). These definitions include the address book fields (currently set at 5) with the main account information.\r Other import scripts specialized towards beginning balance initialization can be found here.\r The HOW TOs contain samples of import procedures to import customers, suppliers, and inventory.\r Related Links\r Importing Data into KSSBooks\r   Exporting Data from KSSBooks'),(171,172,'d','en_us','07.08.07','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/08-Setup/07-Users/UserHome.html','Setup.Users','Setup - Users','Setup - Users\r \r \r \r \r Setup - Users\r KSSBooks user accounts allow for individualized access to the PhreBooks modules. User accounts are used in the audit log, setting access permissions, and permissions for reports. \r When the KSSBooks systems is installed, a single administrator account is added given full permission to access all of the KSSBooks functionality. New users can be added and thier access can be controlled to modules that they are given permission to access. If No Access is given to a function, the option will not appear in their menu when they log in. \r NOTE: When adding new modules, permissions have not been established and the modules will not be visible. Each user account will need to be edited and the appropriate permission added to access the module.\r Adding a User Account \r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Users.\r   Press the Add icon. A new screen will appear with a form to fill out for the new user.\r   Enter a username, email address, and password for the new user.\r   Set the permissions for the user. A tab will appear for each main heading. the permissions are initially set for no access for all modules. Select the permission levels for each module in each tab.\r   Press the Save icon to create the user account.\r \r Editing a User Account\r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Users.\r   Press the Edit icon next to the user to edit. A new screen will appear with a form  fill out for the new user.\r   Edit any user information and security permissions as necesary. If the password will no be changed, leave the password fields blank and no changes will be made to the current password in the database. \r   Press the Save icon to update the user account.\r \r Deleting a User Account\r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Users.\r   Press the Delete icon next to the user to delete. A popup will appear to confirm the selection. \r   Press OK to confirm the selection and the user account will be removed from the database.\r \r Related Links\r &nbsp;'),(172,175,'0','en_us','07.08','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/08-Setup/SetupHome.html','Setup','Setup Home','Setup Home\r \r \r \r \r Setup Home\r Company setup modules allow for customization of KSSBooks to meet the needs of your business. Several modules are included with the standard release of KSSBooks but others may be available for download at http://www.wincompinfotech.com.sg. the standard modules include:\r Languages\r Currencies\r Sales Tax\r Countries\r States/Provinces\r Warehouses\r Shipping\r Payment\r Price Sheets\r ZenCart Interface\r User Maintenance\r &nbsp;'),(173,174,'d','en_us','07.09.01','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/09-Configuration/01-ControlPanel.html','Control Panel','Control Panel','Control Panel     Control Panel &nbsp;'),(174,175,'0','en_us','07.09','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/09-Configuration/ConfigHome.html','Configuration','Configuration','Configuration     Configuration &nbsp;'),(175,0,'0','en_us','07','modules/kssbooks/language/en_us/manual/UserManualHome.html','User Manual','User Manual','User Manual\r \r \r \r \r KSSBooks Users Manual\r Please select a category to view:\r Suppliers - Your suppliers of goods and services. \r Customers - Those that receive you companies goods and services. \r Inventory - The goods and services your company produces/sells.\r Banking - Your financial receivables (customer payments), payables ( customer payments) and activities related to your financial institution. \r General Ledger - The accounting ledgers to track your companies overall performance.\r Employees - Your companies work force, sales reps, and other personnel used to operate your company. \r Setup - Defines the modules activated, security settings, and other parameters needed to tailor KSSBooks to you company. \r Configuration and Defaults - Sets the default information to use throughout KSSBooks. Defined default general ledger accounts, required information, and other initial settings used.'),(176,178,'d','en_us','01.06.07','modules/ksshelp/language/en_us/manual/About.html','Help.About','About KSSHelp','About KSSHelp\r \r \r \r \r \r About  KSSHelp\r KSSHelp Version 1.0\r Released xx/xx/2006\r Developers:\r System Info (Link)'),(177,178,'d','en_us','01.06.07','modules/ksshelp/language/en_us/manual/Contact.html','Help.Contact','Contact KSSHelp','Contact KSSHelp\r \r \r \r \r \r Contact KSSHelp \r SourceForge Links\r KSSHelp Homepage\r Developers email\r &nbsp;'),(178,79,'0','en_us','01.06','modules/ksshelp/language/en_us/manual/Introduction.html','Help.Introduction','KSSHelp Introduction','KSSHelp Introduction\r \r \r \r \r \r Welcome the KSSHelp\r About\r Topics (Links)\r \r   Using Help\r   Help Buttons\r   Search Techniques\r \r Detailed Table of Contents\r Related Links\r \r   Legal Notices\r   Support\r   Contact Information\r   About KSSHelp'),(179,178,'d','en_us','01.06.04','modules/ksshelp/language/en_us/manual/LegalNotices.html','Help.Legal Notices','KSSHelp Lcense','KSSHelp Lcense\r \r \r \r \r \r GNU License \r GPL License Here'),(180,178,'d','en_us','01.06.02','modules/ksshelp/language/en_us/manual/PhreeHelpButtons.html','Help.Buttons','KSSHelp Buttons','KSSHelp Buttons\r \r \r \r \r \r KSSHelp Buttons \r Show the buttons and list how they work and what they do.'),(181,178,'d','en_us','01.06.03','modules/ksshelp/language/en_us/manual/SearchMethods.html','Help.Search Techniques','KSSHelp Search Techniques','KSSHelp Search Techniques\r \r \r \r \r \r Search Techniques \r Help on how to find information, use the search tab.'),(182,178,'d','en_us','01.06.05','modules/ksshelp/language/en_us/manual/Support.html','Help.Support','KSSHelp Support','KSSHelp Support\r \r \r \r \r \r KSSHelp Support \r &nbsp;\r Support BBS\'s and related.'),(183,178,'d','en_us','01.06.01','modules/ksshelp/language/en_us/manual/UsingPhreeHelp.html','Help.Using KSSHelp','Using KSSHelp','Using KSSHelp\r \r \r \r \r \r Using KSSHelp\r This page describes how to use the KSSHelp utility.'),(184,186,'d','en_us','07.04.WO.03','modules/work_orders/language/en_us/manual/builder.html','Inventory.Work Order Builder','Work Order Builder','Work Order Builder\r \r   \r   \r   \r \r   \r   \r \r \r Work Order Builder\r \r The Work Order Builder provides the ability to build templates from\r which items can be assembled. A work\r order template consists of one or more work order tasks in sequence to\r help control the assembly process as an integral part of a quality\r control system.\r \r Adding a Work Order Template\r \r Work order templates are managed through the work order Builder\r screen. To add a template, follow the steps below:\r \r \r \r   Navigate to Inventory -&gt; Work Order Builder. If the\r main screen currently being viewed, click the New\r icon .\r   Fill in the fields as defined:\r      Work Order Title: Contains\r a short title to use for the template. This title is used when\r generating work orders from the pop-up list.\r     SKU: Enter a sku or select\r a sku from the Search pop-up list.\r Note, only skus that are assemblies will appear in the pop-up.\r     Description: This field\r will be filled in automatically if the sku is selected from the pop-up\r window.\r It may be edited, left alone or re-written as necessary to describe the\r work order and display all pertinent information.\r     Revision: This field is\r read-only and will be controlled by the\r module.\r     Use Allocation: Determines\r whether or not to allocate parts with the work order. If Yes\r is selected, the quantity_on_allocation values will be adjusted for all\r parts required to build the assembly.\r     Ref\r Documents: Lists any reference documents that\r provide additional direction/clarification/process control while\r assembling the sku.\r      Ref Drawings: Lists any\r reference drawings that may provide additional\r direction/clarification/process control while assembling the sku.\r   For all the task steps needed populate the procedure\r list to assemble the sku by selecting from the\r list of tasks created with the Work Order Task process. The sequence\r should be the same as what it would take to build the item.\r   Click the Save icon to\r save the task and return to the main\r template list page.\r \r \r Editing a Work Order Template\r \r Work order templates can be edited at any time.\r \r \r \r   Navigate to Inventory -&gt; Work\r Order Builder.\r   Locate the template to be edited, either through the paging\r system or searching.\r   Click on the row to be edited. Note: Some fields will not be\r editable and are locked by the system. This is to maintain quality\r control over the work order process.\r REVISIONS:\r If the work order has been used to build a inventory item. The revision\r will automatically be rolled to the next level. \r   Change the fields as necessary and click the Save icon to\r save the template\r and clear the form.\r \r \r Deleting a Work Order Template\r \r Work order templates can only be deleted if they have not been used\r in a Work Order.\r \r \r \r   Navigate to Inventory -&gt; Work Order Builder.\r   Locate the template to be deleted, either through the paging\r system or searching.\r   Click on Delete icon on\r the work order template to be deleted.\r   Confirm the deletion of the template.\r \r \r Related Topics\r \r \r Work Order Module\r Installing/Removing the Work Order Module\r Work Order Tasks\r Work Order Manager'),(185,186,'d','en_us','07.04.WO.01','modules/work_orders/language/en_us/manual/install.html','Inventory.Work Order Installation','Installing/Removing the Work Order Module','Installing/Removing the Work Order Module\r \r   \r   \r   \r \r   \r   \r \r \r Installing/Removing the Work Order Module\r \r The work order module is a part of the\r KSS Small Business Solution. The module can be installed and\r configured following a few easy steps.\r \r Installation\r \r \r \r   Download and unzip the work_order\r module from the Phreesoft webstore. (www.Phreesoft.com)\r   Copy/upload the work_orders folder to\r the /path_to_kss/modules directory.\r   Navigate to Company -&gt; Module\r Administration.\r   If KSS Module Administration\r permissions have been set to full, click on the Install button next to\r the Work Order title and description.\r   The installation process will begin.\r If successful, the Work Order Module status will turn green and the\r revision information will appear in the Version column of the table.\r   If a Properties icon \r appears, click on the icon and set any properties to configure the\r module.\r \r \r Note: By\r default, your permissions for access to all the module features will be\r set to Full but no other user will be able to access the module until\r individual permissions have been set.\r \r Uninstalling the Work Order Module\r \r To uninstall &nbsp;the Work Order\r module, follow the steps below.\r \r NOTE: Removing the module will also\r remove the work order related database tables and module\r uploaded/create files in the my_files directory.\r \r \r \r   Navigate to Company -&gt; Module\r Administration.\r   If KSS Administration\r permissions have been set to full access, Click on the Uninstall button\r next to the Work Order Module. Confirm the removal of the module and\r the process will begin.\r   If successful, the green highlighting\r will be removed on the Work Order module line. Any error or\r informational messages will appear below the menu bar.\r   OPTIONAL: The uninstall process will\r not remove the module files in the /modules/work_orders directory or\r any files, if they exist, in the my_files/DB_NAME/work_orders\r directory. These files must be removed from the server manually.\r \r \r Related Topics\r \r  Work Order Module\r Work Order Tasks\r Work Order Builder\r Work Order Manager'),(186,149,'0','en_us','07.04.WO','modules/work_orders/language/en_us/manual/main.html','Inventory.Work Orders','Work Order Module','Work Order Module\r \r   \r   \r   \r \r   \r   \r \r \r Work Order Module\r \r The work order module is intended to help control the manufacturing\r process when assembling inventory. Features include:\r \r \r \r   Task driven work flow process\r   Sign-off ability for production workers and quality control\r   Task time tracking for job estimation\r   Revision control for process management\r   Ability to assemble into inventory (create a journal entry\r similar to Inventory -&gt; Assemblies)\r   Uses Quantity of Allocation in inventory to identify lack of\r availability of assembly parts\r   Work Order form lists tasks, sign off requirements, required\r parts and sign off blocks.\r \r \r How\r does it work? Work Orders are broken into a series of tasks. The\r tasks are combined to create a work order template for a given sku.\r The work order template is then executed with statistics, data and\r sign-offs recorded in a work order journal (not associated with the\r main journal of KSSBooks)\r \r Work Order Tasks - Overview\r \r When building a product, the assembly process can be broken into a\r series\r of tasks. These tasks make up the building blocks of the work order.\r Click here for more detailed information regarding work order tasks.\r \r Work Order Builder - Overview\r \r Once the tasks for building an inventory item, the work order\r builder\r sequences the tasks required for assembling a specific product. The\r Work Order Builder only allows one sku for each template. Click here\r for more details on building a work order template. Once a work order\r template has been executed, it must be revised if the process is\r changed. This is for quality control.\r \r Work Order Manager - Overview\r \r The work order manager is the execution of a work order template.\r The\r work order manager tracks the assembly of an inventory item,\r allocates material and assembles item in the inventory database.\r Click here for more information on Work Order Manager.\r \r An Example\r \r We\r want to assemble a bicycle (must be in inventory as an assembly\r already). The steps required (very simply example) are:\r \r \r \r   Pull parts from stock room.\r   Assemble bicycle per assembly procedure.\r   Inspect finished product.\r   Record number of bicycles into inventory database. \r \r \r Step 1: We need to create the tasks using the Work Order Task\r builder\r \r \r \r   Click on Inventory -&gt; Work Order Tasks.\r   Enter information\r on the form Task Name : Pull Parts\r Description : Pull parts as listed on the work\r order form Department : Manufacturing\r (Set up in Company -&gt; Module Administration -&gt; Contacts -&gt;\r Properties -&gt; Maintain Departments tab\r Ref Documents &amp; Ref Drawings : leave blank\r Task Time : 0.5 Hours\r Mfg Sign-off, QA Sign-off, Data Entry &amp;\r ERP Entry : No \r   Press the Save icon to save the task\r \r \r Repeat the above procedure for the remaining 3 steps with the\r following\r differences:\r \r Step 2. Change the task name and description, MFG Sign-off to Yes,\r Data Entry to Yes (for serial numbers)\r \r Step 3: Change the task name and description. QA Sign-off to Yes.\r \r Step 4: Change the task name and description. ERP Entry to Yes.\r \r Step 2: We need to build a template.\r \r \r \r   Click on Inventory -&gt; Work Order Builder\r   Click the New icon\r   Enter the information on the form as follows: Title : Build\r Bicycle SKU : Select\r a SKU from the search pop-up icon. (the bicycle\r assembly needs to be in the Inventory database already), description is\r automatically filled in Use Allocation : Yes Ref Documents &amp; Ref\r Drawings : blank \r   On the first task line, click on the search icon and select Pull\r Parts from the pop-up.\r   Click on the Add a line icon and repeat step 4 for the remaining\r three tasks.\r   Click on the Save icon to save the work order template.\r \r \r Step 3: We need to generate a work order to let manufacturing know\r to build a bicycle.\r \r \r \r   Click on Inventory -&gt; Work Order Manager\r   Click the New icon\r   Click the search icon next to the SKU field and select the Build\r Bicycle work order. The\r title and SKU are filled into the form along with the task list.\r   Enter the number of bicycles to build, we'),(187,186,'d','en_us','07.04.WO.04','modules/work_orders/language/en_us/manual/manager.html','Inventory.Work Order Manager','Work Order Manager','Work Order Manager\r \r   \r   \r   \r \r   \r   \r \r \r Work Order Manager\r \r The work order manager control the work order process through\r manufacturing. Work orders are specific to a sku\r and are reused over and over to manage production work flow, provide\r record keeping, track assembly times and manage inventory.\r \r Creating a Work Order to Build Something\r \r Before you can assemble an inventory item, a work order template\r must exist in the system. \r \r \r \r   Navigate to Inventory -&gt; Work Order Manager.\r   Click on the New icon \r to start the create work order screen.\r   Search for a sku from the pop-up. Only skus that have a work\r order template will appear in the pop-up. Click on the SKU you want to\r assemble.\r   The SKU, Work Order Title will be filled in automatically. also,\r the task list will be displayed after the Comments field. \r   Enter the quantity to assemble.\r   If you use the priority indications, select a priority form the\r drop-down menu.\r   If this work order requires any special instructions, enter them\r in the Work Order Notes and Comments field. Note that these comments\r can be added to, edited or removed during the assembly process.\r   Click the Save icon \r (or Print and save icon )\r to post (and print) the work order.\r \r \r Editing a Work Order\r \r A work order can be edited at any time. However, only some of the\r fields may be altered from when it was originally created.\r \r \r \r   Navigate to Inventory -&gt; Work Order Manager.\r   Locate the work order to be edited, either through the paging\r system or searching.\r   Click on the Edit icon on\r the action column of the work order to be edited. Note:\r Some fields will not be editable and are locked by the system. This is\r to maintain quality control over the work order process.\r   Change the fields as necessary and click the Save icon to\r save the task and\r clear the form.\r \r \r Executing the Steps of a Work Order\r \r A work order must be acted upon to complete the process. &nbsp;To\r act upon a work order:\r \r \r \r   Navigate to Inventory -&gt; Work Order Manager.\r   Locate the work order to act upon and click on the work order\r line or the Build Work Order icon \r to open the build page.\r   The task line that is being worked on will be highlighted. After\r completion of the step, enter the information, as requested by the task\r requirements, and press the Update button.\r   After completion of all task steps of the work order, The work\r order will close and the page will return to the main work order\r manager page.\r \r \r Deleting a Work Order\r \r Work orders can be deleted at any time.\r \r \r \r   Navigate to Inventory -&gt; Work Order Manager.\r   Locate the work order to be deleted, either through the paging\r system or searching.\r   Click on Delete icon on\r the work order to be deleted.\r   Confirm the deletion of the work order.\r \r \r Related Topics\r \r \r   Work Order Module\r   Installing/Removing the Work Order Module\r   Work Order Tasks\r   Work Order Builder'),(188,186,'d','en_us','07.04.WO.02','modules/work_orders/language/en_us/manual/tasks.html','Inventory.Work Order Tasks','Work Order Tasks','Work Order Tasks\r \r   \r   \r   \r \r   \r   \r \r \r Work Order Tasks\r \r Work order tasks are the building block\r of a work order template. \r \r Adding a Work Order Task\r \r Work order tasks are managed through the\r work order task screen. To add a task, follow the steps below:\r \r \r \r   Navigate to Inventory -&gt; Work\r Order Task. If this screen currently being viewed, click the New icon to\r clear the form.\r   Fill in the fields as defined:\r     Task Name: Contains a short\r title to use for the task. This title is used when building work order\r templates.\r     Description:\r Contains a full description of thee task which will appear in the task\r list on the work order manager screen during the work order build\r process and on the work order form that can be printed with each work\r order.\r     Department:\r Contains the responsible department for the task.\r     Ref Documents: Lists any\r reference documents that provide additional\r direction/clarification/process control over the task. \r     Ref Drawings:\r Lists any\r reference drawings that may provide additional\r direction/clarification/process control over the task.\r     Task Time:\r Estimated/expected\r time to complete the task. this is used for statistical measurement of\r task execution time compared with actual execution time.\r     Mfg Signoff:\r Whether or not a\r electronic signoff of the task is required by manufacturing personnel.\r If Yes, requires a user name and password to complete the task step and\r move to the next. If No, the step can be completed with a click of the\r Update button.\r     QA signoff: Whether or not\r a electronic signoff of the\r task is\r required by Quality Assurance personnel. If Yes, requires a user name\r and password to complete the task step and move to the next.\r     Data Entry:\r Whether or not data\r is required to be entered to complete the task step. Measurements,\r dimensions, lot codes, etc may be entered into the database for record\r keeping.\r     ERP Entry:\r Determines whether to assemble the number of units into the ERP\r inventory system. NOTE: This should only be set to Yes once per\r work order template\r to prevent multiple entries into the ERP system.\r   Click the Save icon to\r save the template and clear the form.\r \r \r Editing\r a Work Order Task\r \r Work order tasks can be edited at any\r time. \r \r \r \r   Navigate to Inventory -&gt; Work\r Order Tasks.\r   Locate the task to be edited,\r either through the paging system or searching.\r   Click on the row to be edited.\r   Change the fields as necessary and\r click the Save icon to\r save the task and clear the form.\r \r \r Deleting a Work Order Task\r \r NOTE: Work order tasks can only be\r deleted if they have not been used in a Work Order.\r \r \r \r   Navigate to Inventory -&gt; Work\r Order Tasks.\r   Locate the work order task to be\r deleted, either through the paging system or searching.\r   Click on delete icon on\r &nbsp;the work order task to be deleted.\r   Confirm the deletion of the task.\r \r \r Related Topics\r \r \r Work Order Module\r Installing/Removing the Work Order Module\r Work Order Builder\r Work Order Manager');
